title: angel's hair tomato basil toss
directions: Prepare capellini according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Stir-fry garlic and green onions one minute (do not brown).
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook 2 minutes.
Toss tomato sauce with hot cooked capellini. Serve and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water; add 3/4 cup cold water. Dissolve well; add pineapple and pie filling.
Chill in long dish; cut in squares.
Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: cream of wheat bread(like corn bread!)
directions: Do not use water in this recipe.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender for about 4 seconds or use mixer for about 2 minutes.
Bake in well-greased and floured 9-inch glass pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
For variety, add 1/2 cup coconut.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Combine beans in a casserole dish.
Add ground beef and other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (have substituted with chili beans and butter beans). Also, have substituted cut up hot dogs for the ground beef, but not as good.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt bar.
Stir in rice cereal and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until set.

title: teriyaki chicken and rice
directions: In a small Ziploc bag, combine the 2 tablespoons chicken broth, soy sauce, sugar, vegetable oil, minced garlic and chicken, then seal bag. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Remove chicken from marinade and set marinade aside. Broil chicken for 12 minutes or until juices run clear, turning once. Meanwhile, add broth to marinade to measure 2/3 cup. Pour into a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Add rice and let stand for 5 minutes. Only makes 1 serving.

title: baked spiced carrots
directions: Shred the carrots and place in a buttered casserole.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly; bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: scratch biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening, then add buttermilk. Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead slightly.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: In bowl combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add apple and pecans.
In another bowl combine sugar, milk, oil, lemon juice, vanilla, lemon peel and egg.
Mix well.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into 12 paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Bake at 450° until done.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven or roaster with a tight fitting cover. Mix well. Cover tightly and bake at 250° for 5 hours. Do not stir or open until 5 hours are up. Serves 6.

title: creamy hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours uncovered.

title: spicy barbecues
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook hamburger in skillet until it loses its red color.
Pour off fat.
Add to sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on heated buns.
Serves 8.

title: antipasto dip
directions: In a large saucepan, bring all ingredients to a boil; refrigerate.
Serve in small dip bowl with sturdy, large crackers.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Chop green pepper, onion and dried beef.
Chop garlic.
Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, and chopped items in bowl.
Spread in a baking dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown meat; put meat and rest of ingredients in a casserole bowl.
Cook, uncovered, in oven for 3 hours at 325°.

title: puppy chow snack
directions: Melt together butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over a box of Crispix snack mix; mix well.
Put confectioners sugar in large plastic bag.
Add Crispix mix; shake until coated.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add eggs.
Add lemon and apricot juices. Cook until thick.
Cool.
Layer apricots, cheese and nuts in bottom of mold or 9-inch square pan.
Pour cool dressing over all.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and add a pinch of soda.
Stir well and pour over popped corn.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Roll out on lightly sugared board on counter top.
Spread with peanut butter. Roll up and cut into slices.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend in blender for several seconds. Pour into a greased 10-inch pie pan, or two 8-inch pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Pie forms its own crust.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ena's orange bread
directions: Cut rind into small pieces.
Cover with water in a saucepan and boil for 1/2 hour.
Change the water three times.
Drain and cover with sugar and let set for a short while.
Add egg and melted butter.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk. Place in greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add pineapple juice, water and vinegar.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add beets and pineapple.
Heat thoroughly. Serve hot or cold.
Yields 10 servings.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Mix together shrimp and cream cheese.
Add the rest of the ingredients and blend with a fork until well mixed.
Shape into a square or oblong dish and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
When ready to serve, pour 1 cup of shrimp cocktail sauce over the top. Serve with crackers.

title: helen seaton's haupia(hawaiian coconut pudding)
directions: Put coconut into small saucepan; add milk.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat; let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour or overnight. Whirl in blender for 2 minutes.
Pour into medium saucepan.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt and drained pineapple.
Bring to simmer. Combine pineapple juice and cornstarch; add to milk mixture and cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally so there are no lumps.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan to cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: vermicelli soup
directions: Chop garlic and onion.
Heat the oil in a 2-quart saucepan and lightly brown vermicelli.
Watch carefully and stir constantly to prevent burning.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute for several minutes.
Add tomatoes, stock, chiles and pimiento.
Simmer about 8 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Serve hot. Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: no filler crab cakes
directions: Check crabmeat for shells.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Shape into cakes.
Broil 5 minutes.
Serve with tartar or cocktail sauce.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan over low heat stir together first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly, bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press into pan.
Cool.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Makes 32.

title: chocolate shortcake
directions: Sift sugar, flour together.
Mix in saucepan the margarine, oil and cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Add and mix well the buttermilk, vanilla, eggs, salt and soda.
Spray a long pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Top with corn flake crumbs mixed with melted shortening.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Should be bubbly around the edges.

title: canned steak
directions: Bring water, salt and brown sugar to a boil; cool.
Put a cup of brine into each quart jar.
Fill with cubed meat or steak. Process in a pressure cooker for 45 minutes at 10 pounds pressure. This doesn't have to be processed as long because of the brine.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Mix sauce ingredients in glass jar and
shake well.
Lay wings side by side in large pan (or two pans) so they are in a single layer.
Pour sauce over them and marinate 4 hours or overnight. Bake until done at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: taco "volcano" dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
Mix and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Spoon sour cream mixture into middle of large plate. Spread over plate.
Cover sour cream mixture with green chilies and cheeses.
Top with diced tomatoes and sliced black olives.
Serve with taco chips or rye bread.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute until brown the butter, onion and mushrooms.
Add ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Blend in cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Mix together the next 4 ingredients and sprinkle over the sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sourdough starter(amish, herman)
directions: Dear Whomever:
Read this before opening the dish to say "hello" to Herman.
I give you this gift and hope you can treat my friend Herman the way he is accustomed to being treated.
Each day you need to do something special for Herman so that on the 10th day, he will treat you with respect.
So on the first day feed Herman:

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand; beat slightly with mixer. Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spinach with yogurt and spices(palak raita)
directions: Wash spinach well and remove any tough stems. Pull the leaves into pieces and put into a saucepan with the moisture on the leaves or add 1 tablespoon of water.
Cover and steam over low heat until spinach is tender.
Drain and chop finely.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well and pour in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: n' awlins boiled crawfish
directions: Empty your crawfish in a No. 3 wash tub and cover them completely with cold water.
Wash them several times, using fresh water each time, at least four or five times until the water comes clean.
Drain off last rinse water completely, and get your boiler ready.
In a large
90 to 102 quart pot, put in enough water to completely cover the crawfish when they are added and bring it to a rapid boil.
Then toss in the first eight ingredients and boil them for about 15 minutes.
You want the flavors to mix and create a seasoned stock.
Next, drop in the lagniappe - corn on the cob, new potatoes and smoked sausage.
Add carrots if desired.
Let it cook for about 15 minutes.
When all the extras are three- quarters done,
add the crawfish and cover the pot.
The water will stop boiling immediately.
When the water comes back to a full boil, time your crawfish for about two minutes, shut off fire, and remove it from the burner.
Then drop some crushed ice on top of the crawfish for about 25 minutes.
It is a good idea to try one every five minutes or so to keep the crawfish from getting too spicy for your taste.

title: frecken doodles
directions: Rise a loaf of frozen bread.
Heat vegetable oil to 270° or where you do doughnuts.
Put powdered sugar in a bowl; add almond extract and boiling water to make right icing consistency.
In another bowl, mix equal amounts of brown sugar, granulated sugar and cinnamon.
In a third bowl, put in powdered sugar.
Pull off a piece of bread; stretch and drop in oil.
Turn and brown on both sides; take out and drop in icing or whatever sugar you want.

title: candy pecan rolls(soft center)
directions: Mix powdered sugar, Marshmallow Creme, almond and vanilla. Knead until stiff.
Shape into rolls and freeze.
Melt caramels and 2 tablespoons water in double boiler.
Dip rolls in caramel and immediately roll in chopped pecans.

title: almond chicken
directions: Pat chicken dry with paper towels.
Cut into strips 1/2-inch wide by 3-inches long.
Stir soy sauce, rice wine, chicken stock, sugar, cornstarch, ginger and garlic together.
Place chicken in marinade, turning to coat.
Marinate at least 1 hour, turning chicken after half an hour.
Remove chicken from marinade and drain on paper towels.
Beat egg slightly with 1/2 teaspoon water.
One by one, dip chicken pieces in egg and roll in almonds to coat.
Let almond coated pieces set 15 minutes.

title: wilted dandelion green salad
directions: Wash greens, discarding stems.
Pat dry and tear into bite size pieces to make about 6 cups.
Place greens in large bowl. Add onions and freshly ground pepper.
Cover and chill thoroughly. At serving, cook bacon in deep skillet until crisp.
Slowly stir in vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Add dandelion mixture. Toss until leaves are coated and slightly wilted (not cooked), 1 to 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped egg.

title: pull-a-part bread with cinnamon and pecans
directions: Spray Bundt pan with nonstick spray.
Layer a few pecans on the bottom and sprinkle some cinnamon and sugar on top.
Cut each biscuit in fourths.
Roll each piece in cinnamon/sugar mixture thoroughly in pan.
After doing can, sprinkle butter and more pecans.
Layer more biscuits, butter and pecans.
Pan should be half full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and dump onto plate.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake(doris' favorite)
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add cream cheese, beating well until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: pastry - perfect every time(for a one crust baked pie shell)
directions: Stir together flour and
salt.
Cut
in shortening to a crumb consistency.
Sprinkle
water
onto
mixture.
Toss with fork until all is moistened.
Form
dough
into
a ball.
Roll out onto a lightly
floured
surface to approximately 1/8 inch thick. Place into a
9-inch
pie
plate;
crimp edges.
Prick bottom and sides with fork several times.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Set on rack to cool.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Slowly mix cornstarch with bacon and water, cooking until thick.
Great with lettuce, dandelion or endive.
Dandelion or endive should be added to hot mixture and set awhile before serving.

title: swedish spritz
directions: Cream butter, then cream in sugar.
Add vanilla and egg, then add dry sifted ingredients.
Force through cookie press or chill. Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° until set, not brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: corn mexicola
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: sara's punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake, following directions on box. Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans. When cool, cut each layer in two, making four layers. Mix in the following order in a large punch bowl: One layer of cake (crumbled), sliced bananas, 1 cup pineapple and 1 cup strawberries. Repeat, using another layer of cake. Once 2 layers are done, sprinkle with 1/2 of pudding mixture and 1/2 of Cool Whip. Repeat, using the other 2 layers of cake. Top with rest of pudding mixture and Cool Whip. Put nuts (chopped) on top and cherries, if desired.

title: pralines
directions: Combine in saucepan both sugars, water, corn syrup, vinegar and salt.
Turn control to highest setting to bring mixture to full boil, stirring constantly.
The second the mixture boils, turn the control to "off."
Let stand for 3 minutes without lid. Do not stir during these 3 minutes.
Immediately stir in vanilla, butterscotch morsels and pecans.
Stir until morsels are dissolved.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
It will look thin.
Work fast and have everything ready because this hardens fast.

title: slow ball dip
directions: With sharp knife, cut top from bread, set aside. Hollow loaf, leaving a 1 1/2 to 2 inch thick shell; cut removed bread in cubes (see note), set both aside.

title: chili con queso
directions: Mix 1/3 Velveeta, 1/3 Cheddar and 1/3 sauce.
Alternate layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with chips (nachos).

title: gayle's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine the sugar, flour and salt in heavy saucepan. Mix well, using the back of the spoon to break up any small lumps of flour. Add the egg yolks but don't mix yet. As you gradually add the milk, stir yolks into the dry ingredients until you get a smooth mixture. Cook over medium to medium-high heat, stirring constantly, for about 5 minutes, or until thickened. Remove from the heat. Stir in the vanilla, butter, and coconut. Pour into the baked pie shell. Preheat oven to 350 degrees for
browning the meringue.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, and molasses.
Add in salt, nutmeg and cinnamon, mix well.

title: toast
directions: Put the bread in the toaster.
Push the button down.
When it's done, it just pops up.
Put butter and cinnamon on it.
Then you eat it.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave:
Microwave margarine in 4-quart bowl or casserole on High 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well. Microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Mix well; scrape bowl.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes; stir after 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in chocolate until melted. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: sausy strawberry shake
directions: Put strawberries in blender container.
Blend until smooth; add milk.
Cover and blend.
Add ice cream and process.
Pour into glasses.

title: egg white meringue
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.
Spread the meringue on top of pie.
Put in oven and brown lightly.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar. Blend in melted mixture.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together. Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Grease pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: nutty pasta
directions: Cover bottom of frying pan with olive oil.
Add garlic, peppers and pine nuts.
Saute until pine nuts are golden.
Add basil.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Refrigerate until party congealed.	Stir in remaining ingredients and refrigerate until congealed.

title: orange surprise salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in sour cream.	Add drained fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: holiday cake salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 2 cups.
Heat in a saucepan.
Add jellos; stir to dissolve.
Blend in cream cheese in blender on low speed.
Add fruits and nuts. Add cake mix; stir all together.
Pour in pan and chill.
Freezes well.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save about 1 pint of broth (skimmed). Saute onion and bell pepper in 1 tablespoon butter for 3 to 5 minutes in a large skillet or heavy pan.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and enough of the broth to make a medium sauce.
Add the chicken and seasonings (salt, pepper and garlic).
Boil 2 minutes.
Crumble enough Doritos to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan about 1/2-inch thick.
Pour chicken mixture over the Doritos and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbling.
Good with Mexican potatoes and beans.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg whites, oil, milk and 1 can coconut in mixer bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Punch holes in warm cake.
Pour cream of coconut over top. Cool.

title: beef dip
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Let set in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain liquid from cherries and pineapple into saucepan with 2 packages of jello. Bring to a boil. Set aside and add cream cheese. Melt cream cheese. Add cherries, pineapple and nuts and then add Coke. Let jell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place meat in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square or 2-quart casserole dish.
For stuffing, combine croutons, celery and onion in bowl.
Add butter and 1/2 cup water; toss until croutons are moistened.
Reserve about 1 1/2 cups stuffing; spread remainder over meat.
Blend soup and 1/4 cup water.
Pour over stuffing.
Top with reserved stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Blend in flour, then continue adding ingredients (half and half, garlic, cheese, tomato sauce, broccoli and mushrooms).
Mix well.
Simmer for about 1 hour, until thick.
Add cooked, drained pasta.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all together for 2 minutes.
Pour in lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: quick cooked cabbage
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat bacon fat or oil.
Add cabbage, salt and pepper.
Toss several times or until cabbage is coated with fat.
Cook, covered, about 3 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Use 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine first four ingredients.
Place in microwave and bring to a boil, about 1 minute and 45 seconds.
Continue to boil 2 minutes on High. Remove and stir in soda.
Place corn in grocery bag.
Pour syrup over corn.

title: juicy fruit salad
directions: In large bowl (preferably a punch bowl), add frozen fruit, fresh bananas, fresh strawberries, pineapple and pineapple juice. Let stand 20 minutes, then serve.
Great at barbecues.

title: microwave harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Pour beet liquid into a 1-cup glass measure and add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid. Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper, and vinegar in a 1-quart microproof casserole or bowl.
Stir in beet liquid.
Cook uncovered, on High (maximum power) for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens and is clear.
Add beets and stir lightly.
Cover and cook on High (maximum power) for about 3 minutes, or until beets are hot.

title: jelled cucumber - cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the hot water.
Let set until cool.
Whip in the mayonnaise.
Add vegetables.
Pour into oblong dish or individual molds.
Refrigerate until set.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine Pet milk, mustard, Velveeta, salt, pepper, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan.
Over low-medium heat, melt cheese to make sauce.
Pour mixture over ham and potatoes. Bake about 20 minutes at 350° until casserole bubbles.
Let cook about 20 minutes to allow to thicken.
Makes 8 moderate servings.

title: mini hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 3 pieces.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and water.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes. You may use mini hot dogs (2 1/2 to 3 pounds).

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Lay pork chops in bottom of pan.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on box.
Put stuffing on top of pork chops.
Heat can of mushroom soup and water together.
Bring to boil.
Pour soup over pork chops and stuffing.
Cover with foil.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli using package directions; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth; cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in cream and wine.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg well. Add other ingredients; mix well. Heat griddle. Cook and enjoy.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Chill overnight and serve with Frito Scoops.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve in ring of poppy seed noodles on hot platter.
Garnish with parsley bouquet.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cook ground beef and onions; drain. Add listed ingredients and pour half into 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer with cheese. Pour remaining half of mixture over cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bette dierolf's nut loaf
directions: Leave nuts and dates whole, do not chop.
Drain cherries; add dates, cherries and nuts.
Cook fruit and nut mixture with flour. Beat eggs and add vanilla.
Mix egg mixture with flour mixture (easiest to do with your hands).
Spoon mixture into 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Slices better if stored for a while.

title: zucchini squash cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light colored.
Add oil until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture. Beat 2 minutes.
Add nuts, vanilla and squash (squeezed in paper towel).
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Blend 1 cup powdered sugar plus 1 tablespoon milk until smooth.
Drizzle over cooled cake.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done but do not overcook.
Drain; set aside.
In frying pan, add oil, garlic and ginger.
Saute 1 1/2 minutes.
Add chicken; continue to saute over low heat 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add sugar and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until thick.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Boil the
first
ingredients
a few minutes.
Remove from heat; add Miracle Whip.
Will last 2 weeks if sealed in a jar in refrigerator.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Fry Owens sausage; crumble in large skillet.
Add some margarine.
Cook sausage until brown.
Add the frozen hash brown potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir well on medium heat.
Cook until done.
Beat eggs well and stir in potato mixture.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Chop pecans. Sprinkle on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle coconut on top of pecans.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box and spread on top of pecans and coconut. Spread cream cheese mixture on cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares and serve.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Put on your favorite icing.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs.
Mix together yolks, bacon, onions, mustard and mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika and top with olive halves.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop vegetables, mix all ingredients and let stand several hours in the refrigerator. Will keep for a week

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with tomato sauce and bake about 1 hour in moderate oven at 350°.
Serve with tossed green salad and garlic bread.
Serve sherbet for dessert.

title: pork with sauerkraut
directions: Roast ham/pork in a warm oven, 325°
for 1 1/2 hours.
Saute onion in oil.
Add sauerkraut and cook for 5 minutes.
Add stock, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
May thicken with cornstarch. Serve with sliced ham.

title: light beer stew
directions: Cut meat into cubes.
Coat heavy pan with cooking spray; add oil.
Place over medium-high heat.
When oil is hot, add meat; cook until well browned, turning to cook on all sides.
Reduce heat to medium-low; add onion and cook until onion is tender and lightly browned.
Stir in beer, spices, carrots and mushrooms; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Combine cornstarch and water; stir until blended.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serves 4.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix together and add a couple of teaspoons of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: oriental beef strips
directions: Brown steak.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, soy sauce, sugar, pepper and garlic.
Cover and cook slow for 45 minutes.
Add carrots, green peppers, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Use cornstarch and water to thicken liquid for gravy. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine 4 ingredients using pineapple juice to make dip right thickness. Dip any fruit that you wish.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add fruit cocktail and egg.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 60 minutes.
Delicious served with whipped cream.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and garlic in oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt and oregano.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Alternate layers of noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
This fills a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: orange carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water until tender. Combine remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until thick and bubbly.
Pour over hot carrots and stir gently to coat carrots. Serves 4.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Float ice on top.

title: any fruit cobbler(so easy and so fast)
directions: In bowl mix first 4 ingredients well.
Melt oleo in pan you are going to bake cobbler in.
Pour any fruit, peaches, blackberries (my favorite), cooked apples etc. over oleo.
Pour the milk, flour etc. over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can top with Cool Whip or eat plain.

title: sure success dessert
directions: Mix the ingredients and serve for dessert or breakfast.

title: corn salad
directions: Can mix all together the night before, but add the mayonnaise just before serving.

title: no-bake pineapple dessert
directions: Combine butter and sugar in mixer bowl; mix well.
Beat in egg.
Fold in undrained pineapple and whipped topping.
Arrange 1 layer of vanilla wafers in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread pineapple mixture in prepared dish.
Crush remaining vanilla wafers. Sprinkle over top.
Chill overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: jew bread
directions: Add flour to cooked sugar mixture, eggs, vanilla and nuts. Bake in a 9x13-inch pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place mixture over chicken and cover dish.
Bake at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Uncover for at least 15 minutes of baking unless juices have cooked down to almost nothing.
Serves 4.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add beet juice and orange juice.
Cook until thickens.
Add beets and butter.
Cook 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: marie's stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 3-quart casserole, combine first four ingredients; mix well and bake.
Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain; toss with butter.
To serve, spread noodles on a large platter and top with stew.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry snow candy
directions: Melt chocolate according to package directions.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let it set until dry.

title: lemonade chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine lemonade concentrate, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in lemonade mixture.
Put pieces on the grill over medium hot coals.
Grill for about 30 minutes. Keep on turning pieces until done.
Before they are done, brush mixture on chicken pieces frequently for last 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Mix well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition.
Add walnuts if desired.
Pour into greased 3-quart Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans (3/4 full).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place in baking dish. Top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Sprinkle about 2 teaspoons minced garlic and dry parsley on chicken.
Squeeze 8 lemons and pour lemon juice to cover chicken.
Let stand as long as possible (at least 20 minutes; better overnight).
Melt butter in skillet (might need 2 skillets).
Throw chicken and juice into pan and cook on highest heat, then lower to medium.
Cut up garlic cloves and throw into pan.
Do not brown.
When cooked, remove garlic and serve with fresh chopped parsley.

title: crab spread
directions: Shred Sea Stix in blender.
Soften cream cheese and cream. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add Sea Stix.

title: salisbury steak deluxe
directions: In bowl, combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce; blend well.
Set aside.
In another bowl, lightly beat egg.
Add bread crumbs, onions, salt and pepper.
Take 1/4 cup of soup mixture and add to ground beef; mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.
In large skillet, brown patties with oil.
Combine remaining soup with water.
Pour over patties.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is done.
Remove and sprinkle with parsley.

title: chris hayden's scallops
directions: Arrange scallops in broil proof baking pan.
Sprinkle with your favorite bread crumbs, seasoned or not.
Melt 1/2 stick butter per pound of scallops and pour over crumbed scallops.
Broil 10 minutes fairly close to heat.

title: chicken (or turkey) casserole
directions: Combine celery, onion, butter or margarine and hot tap water. Add to stuffing mix, chicken or turkey and water chestnuts, then mix together soup and cream of chicken with milk.
Put 1/2 of the stuffing mixture in bottom of
9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add chicken or turkey and sliced water chestnuts.
Layer last 1/2 of stuffing mixture on top.
Pour over milk and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: artichoke squares
directions: One and one-half hours before serving:
Drain liquid from artichokes into 1-quart saucepan.
Drain liquid from second jar and discard.
Finely chop artichokes and set aside.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cook minced onion in artichoke juice until tender.
Beat eggs with a fork in medium bowl.
Stir in cooked onion, chopped artichokes, Mozzarella cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture evenly in baking dish. If not baking right away, cover and refrigerate.

title: pita pizza sandwiches
directions: Cook pepperoni in skillet and drain on paper towels.
Combine pepperoni and cheese in ovenproof pan.
Chop tomatoes and add to pan.
Include juices left on cutting board but not the juice drained from the can.
Sprinkle on Italian seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat in a 350° oven about 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Lightly toast pita pocket, open and fill with mixture.

title: broccoli-carrot slaw
directions: In a mixing bowl, whisk together the sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss in the broccoli slaw and carrots.
Mix to combine well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover and chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: wheat buns
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and heat just until Crisco is melted.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Mixture should be just warm, then add yeast.
Beat well until yeast is dissolved.
Add well beaten eggs; beat well.
Add 3 cups flour and 1 cup wheat flour.
Let raise 3 hours.
Knead.
Roll about 3/8-inch and cut in desired shapes. Put on greased cookie sheets.
Let raise about 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Bring water and sugar to a boil and thicken with paste.
(Let cool.)
Put in 3 cups of blueberries and pour into cooled pie shell.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
lukewarm water.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until it is coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk	and yeast water.
Stir quickly with fork until soft dough is formed.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll	out 1/2-inch thick; cut.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in dish.
Top with Ritz crackers, crushed.
Pour 1 stick margarine over this and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine and put all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Drain off fat.
Add soup and heat again.
Add sour cream.
Serve over cooked macaroni or noodles.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: This dip is done in layers.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar in a mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in bananas.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk and pecans, mixing well after each addition.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger-lentil soup
directions: Combine lentils (rinsed and drained), 2 teaspoons salt, bay leaf and water. Boil, then simmer 45 minutes. Brown hamburger with onion, parsley, garlic powder, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Combine with lentils. Add tomatoes, carrots and celery. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Blend butter with sugar and flour; add egg yolks, lemon juice, lemon peel and milk.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes, plus turn off oven and leave pie inside 20 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients and add crushed pineapple. Add tidbit pineapple.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the butter and cream cheese; cream until fluffy.
Gradually add the sugar and hand mix until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, hand mix well. Add the flour and vanilla.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water until almost tender (about 12 to 14 minutes).
Combine rice with remaining ingredients, stirring well. Spoon mixture into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: bert and ben's sweet and sour green beans
directions: Open the cans of green beans.
Pour out the liquid from 1 of the cans and reserve the liquid from the other can.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients into batter.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all together except crumbs.
Put into casserole and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets (about 1/2 teaspoon per cookie).
Place in oven.
Immediately turn off oven and leave cookies at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Melt margarine; add stuffing mix.
Stir to mix.
Sprinkle on top of veggies.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Then add the rest of the ingredients. Mix well. Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° until done.

title: holland coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugars, salt, nutmeg and oil. Take out 3/4 cup of mixture and add pecans and cinnamon. Save this mixture for topping. To remaining mixture, add buttermilk, soda and egg. Pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan. Sprinkle topping on before baking. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or test with toothpick for doneness.

title: onion casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onions and pepper; cook until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Cover; bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft. Cook chopped broccoli; drain.
Add onion-celery mix, mushrooms, mushroom soup, milk and jalapeno cheese.
Heat.
When cheese melts, soup is ready.
Serve with hard rolls or brown fruit bread.

title: impossible pie
directions: Brown onions and beef and put in a greased pie pan.
(I use more beef and cook in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.)
Mix milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Pour this mixture over meat mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine	crumbs and butter, press onto bottom
of	9-inch	 spring-form
pan.
Bake
minutes. Combine cream cheese, sugar, pumpkin, vanilla, spices and salt; mixing at medium speed until well
blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each
addition.	Pour over crust.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Loosen
cake
from
rim.	Remove rim of pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: praline pecans
directions: Place pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Salt. Heat at 250° for 5 minutes. In a large saucepan, melt butter. Over medium heat, stir in maple syrup and 1/4 cup sugar until boiling. Allow to boil for 5 minutes over low heat. Stir in pecans, stirring to coat evenly. Return to cake pan. Bake at 250°, stirring frequently to prevent clumping. Turn out onto plastic wrap, separating quickly with forks. When cool, dip into sugar.

title: red beans and rice creole style
directions: Wash beans. Soak beans in water overnight.
Brown sausage in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat. Add onions and garlic to pan and cook until tender.
Add beans and soaking liquid, salt, marjoram, bay leaf and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are almost tender.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix as directed and spread over cream cheese mixture.

title: rich chocolate cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the pudding and pie filling and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture comes to a full boil.

title: breakfast blender drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth and creamy.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together 1 cup corn oil, sugar and eggs.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Combine these 2 mixtures.
Blend to mix well.
Add carrots, walnuts and drained pineapple to mixture.
Blend well.
Pour batter into a microwave-safe Bundt cake dish.
Microwave, covered, at High power for about 3 minutes.
Remove cover.
Microwave for another 12 to 14 minutes at High power, letting cake rest for 2 minutes after 5 minutes of microwaving.
Remove cake from oven.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Let cool.
Frost cake when cool. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: orange glazed chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken; stir-fry until lightly browned.
Mix cornstarch, broth, juice, soy sauce, sugar, ginger and garlic powder in medium bowl until smooth.
Stir in skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil on medium heat; boil 1 minute.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, sryup and water until threads.
Then pour in peanuts.
Cook until amber color.
Quickly pour in soda (level) and mix well.
Pour quickly on buttered cookie sheet.

title: kentucky fruit pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, Cool Whip and lemon juice in a large bowl; beat 2 to 3 minutes on medium speed.
Drain pineapple and oranges. Add to mixture.
Add coconut and nuts to mixture.
Add the bananas and stir together.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: french chocolate cream dessert
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and set aside. Cream the butter thoroughly; add sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla and nuts; blend.
Add melted chocolate.
Fold egg whites into creamed mixture.
Cover bottom of pan with crumbs.
Add creamed mixture.
Top with more crumbs and additional nuts, if desired.
Chill several hours or freeze.
Serve cut in squares and topped with whipped cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple cinnamon chips
directions: Cut the apples into 1 centimeter thick strips, then sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on the strips.
After that, cook until brown, not black.

title: louisiana corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in well-greased pan for approximately 35 to 40 minutes at 450°.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Peel and cut watermelon rind into cubes.
Cover with sugar and let stand overnight.
Cook about 3 hours.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: grandma strait's coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; then add oil.
Mix well with fingers, taking out 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.
Add to mixture the buttermilk, egg, baking soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured pans.
Sprinkle crumbs on top; pat into dough.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 325° in greased and floured Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place margarine in pan and melt.
Add milk; bring to boil. Add sugar and vanilla.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn heat off.
Put chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix until melted.
Put in buttered pan and cut before cold.

title: roast chicken rignato a la contessa
directions: Squeeze lemon juice on chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Set aside at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Place chicken in a small roasting pan with olive oil and butter. Sprinkle with oregano.
Roast in a preheated 325° oven, basting frequently for about 1 hour.
Add potatoes and bake 1 hour longer. (Chicken should be well cooked.) Turn occasionally to brown on all sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Coat chicken with seasoned salt.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Add wine and mushrooms.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese and onion rings.
Serve immediately.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and fruit cocktail.
Mix gently.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandmother's potatoes and squash
directions: Saute onions until golden in large frypan. Add potatoes and squash (tomatoes, if desired).
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Occasionally turn vegetables carefully with spatula. Ready to serve with potatoes are soft.

title: pickled squash (yellow)
directions: Slice squash in thin slices.
Add chopped onion and peppers. Cover with 1 tablespoon salt for 1 hour.
Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add pimentos for color.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in bars and cool.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, spices and sugar; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add pumpkin, vegetable oil and bran flakes; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly in ungreased 10 x 4-inch tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: shrimp parmigiana
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Clean and butterfly shrimp.
Grease pan with margarine.
Dip shrimp in oil and then bread crumbs.
Add pepper and garlic powder.
Place in pan.
Bake 3 minutes.
Take out.
Add tomato sauce and then slice of Mozzarella.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Squeeze lemon before serving.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Brown meat in oil in a heavy saucepan, chopping up large pieces with a spatula. Add onions and cook until soft. Add tomatoes, water, spices and beans. Cook over low heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking. Serve over rice or spaghetti. Garnish with grated cheese.

title: creole dressing mix
directions: Run meat
through grinder;
melt 1 stick margarine in a Dutch oven
and
fry meat until brown.
Add onions, celery and garlic; stir
and
cook until soft.
Add Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and
stick
margarine; stir well.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 2 hours.	Season to taste.
(Serves 12.)

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple and bananas.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch serving container or glass dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over top of mixture and chill until firm.
Nuts may be added if desired. Serves 8 to 10.
Excellent with ham or turkey or as dessert.

title: candied walnuts
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together the sugar, corn syrup and water.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat, until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, to 235° on a candy thermometer or until a small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt and walnuts; stir until mixture begins to thicken and turns white.
Pour onto a well-greased cookie sheet and separate into clusters.
Cool and store in a tightly covered tin box.
Makes one pound.

title: potluck chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream. Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine crumbs, butter and celery seed. Sprinkle over chicken mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly. Garnish with parsley and red peppers, if desired. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Cut artichoke hearts into 4 pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Top with seasoned breadcrumbs.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Leave covered.
Just before serving, remove foil and mix all ingredients.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans.
Let soak overnight.
Add salt pork to beans; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in onion, green onions, parsley, garlic salt, oregano, red pepper, hot sauce and tomato sauce; continue to cook 1 hour.
Brown sausage and drain; add to bean mixture.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, adding more water, if necessary.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Roll skinless chicken breast in all-purpose coating mix.
Melt small amount of butter in baking dish.
Add coated chicken.
Cover with Thousand Island dressing (thinned with a small amount of water).

title: russian tea("granny blackstock's recipe")
directions: Make tea as usual (unsweetened). Extract juice from lemon and oranges.
Boil rinds with cloves in 1 pint of water.
Strain and add with juices and sugar to tea.
"Delicious." Serve hot or cold.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Prepare and bake pastry shell.
After removing from oven, reduce temperature to 350°.

title: brownies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter, margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Turn off heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Blend milk and peanut butter.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly at low speed for 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream and peanuts.

title: green bean medley
directions: Heat 1-inch water to boiling in medium saucepan.
Add beans and carrots.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until almost tender, about 12 minutes.
Drain.
Cook and stir onion and mushrooms in margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Stir in beans, carrots and salt.
Cook, covered over medium heat until tender.

title: apricot delight
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Bring pineapple to boil.
Add sugar and jello.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until slightly set. Blend in milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream all together and make 3 to 6 balls.
Roll balls in chopped nuts, chili powder, fresh parsley or paprika.

title: clam chowder
directions: Open clams and chop.
Bring water to a boil, add potatoes, celery, parsley, celery salt and pepper and simmer 20 minutes. While this cooks, cut and fry bacon until lightly brown.
Add onion and saute 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour, stirring until it disappears.
Blend in milk, clams and clam liquor, stirring until slightly thickened.
Set aside until vegetables finish cooking....then add to soup pot and serve.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Makes a double recipe.
Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add soups and let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sour cream to mixture; simmer again for 5 to 10 minutes more.
Cook noodles and drain.
Place noodles on plate and pour sauce over noodles.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in quart jar.
Use 3 teaspoons to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: great pasta
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain linguine and put in a large bowl (keep warm).

title: jessica's chicken
directions: Wrap 2 pieces of bacon around each chicken breast.
Place side by side in greased pan.
Sprinkle with beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 225° for 3 1/2 hours.
Garnish with mushrooms and parsley.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces.
Cook as directed and drain.
Chop chicken and combine with pimento, onion, salt, pepper, cheese and spaghetti.
Lightly toss until well mixed.
Put into baking dish and sprinkle with retained cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
(Will freeze.)

title: lemon cream dressing(makes about 10 ounces)
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in double boiler.
Add beaten egg and let cool.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Turn on wax paper.
Cover with coconut.
Form into 2 1/2-inch roll.
Cover with coconut.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill and cut into slices.
Can be frozen.

title: chili relleno
directions: Fill seeded green chilies with sliced Cheddar cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add flour and egg yolks, beating until creamy.
Dip chilies into batter and fry in hot oil until brown. Serve with taco sauce.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and chocolate.
Add boiling water.
Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter; beat well.
Cool.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown in oven.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onion in oil; add turkey or ham and tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer the mixture, beginning and ending with mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter, bread crumbs and/or cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and cook until smooth. Beat eggs; add milk, cheese, baking powder, salt, sugar and the butter-flour mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients when cheese softens.
Roll into a ball.
Then roll in chopped ham.

title: rum or bourbon balls(servings:  120)
directions: Blend wafers in blender and put in bowl and add chopped pecans.
Add cocoa, sugar, Karo and rum.
Mix well and make into little bite size balls, about 1-inch.
Store in refrigerator for one or two weeks for better blended flavor.

title: sukiyaki(serves 4)
directions: Cook udon noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Use plenty of water.
Cut up vegetables in large bite size pieces.
(They will shrink when you cook them.)
Cut tofu in 1 x 1-inch cubes.
Keep vegetables separate.
Heat wok on medium-high.
Put whole bottle of sukiyaki sauce in wok.
Add beef. (Keep on one side of wok.)
Cook 5 minutes.
Add vegetables, tofu and udon.
Keep separate in wok while cooking.
Don't mix.
After all items are cooked, serve in bowls.
For shiitake, shungiku and shirataki, check your local yellow pages under Japanese Food Products.

title: cole slaw(dietetic)
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot and onion in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a small bowl.
After mixing ingredients together, add contents of small bowl to the contents of the large bowl.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Yield:
10 servings.
Exchanges:
1 vegetable, 1 1/2 fat.
Calories per serving:

title: dip for fresh fruits
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, marshmallow cream and orange juice with mixer until
smooth.
Refrigerate.
Use
any
fresh fruit: peaches, apples,
grapes
(green
seedless), pineapple chunks, bananas, melons, strawberries, etc.

title: artichoke dip 2
directions: Cut artichoke hearts in fourths.
Mix all ingredients together except paprika.
Put in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Gradually pour in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
In casserole dish, put 1/2 the cooked cabbage.
Cover with sliced cheese.
Add one half the white sauce.
Add another layer of cabbage, cheese and remainder of white sauce.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve as a salad or a vegetable.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites.
To first mix, add lemon zest, egg yolks, milk and lemon juice.
Add egg whites.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish or 6 custard cups; place in cake pan with 1-inch of water.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with dollop of whipped cream.

title: tuna or crab hero sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna or crab, mayonnaise, parsley, sour cream, lemon juice and garlic salt. Slice French bread lengthwise into 2 pieces. Place on baking sheet. Spread with butter. Spread on tuna or crab mixture. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars. Add egg; blend in salad oil. Blend in oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts. Stir until mixed. Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Mix well. Form into balls the size of walnuts. Place on ungreased sheet and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° about 12 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yields approximately 140 cookies.

title: cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cranberries in hot water (jello first, then berries). Add crushed pineapple and orange juice. Stir in nuts. Pour into 9 x 13 glass or plastic dish (not metal). Chill until very firm. Frost with topping. Sprinkle with additional nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour half of soup mixture over rice.
Layer chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aliza's daddy's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add ingredients in order given, blending after each.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together crumbs and 6 tablespoons melted butter.
Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat until fluffy: confectioners sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Spread over crumbs. Slice bananas and place over creamy filling.
Spread pineapple evenly over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Decorate with cherries.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in butter.
Mix together with the remaining ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil and grease.
Put rice on bottom.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups and pour over rice (do not dilute).
Sprinkle on onion soup mix.
Shake pan to mix.
Seal foil tight and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, cream and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll and cut into shapes.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: snacks
directions: Wrap each of the first 3 ingredients with 1/2 slice of bacon. Broil until bacon is cooked and serve warm.
Put toothpick in to hold bacon in place.
They can be used to hold while eating.

title: jalapeno spinach casserole
directions: Add flour, water, milk, pepper and salt to onions and blend. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add spinach and put in casserole. Top with buttered bread crumbs and brown in oven.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix and add until desired flavor.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Beat until smooth in large bowl.
Beat in milk and instant pudding.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: cheese canapes
directions: Split muffins and spread with mixture.
Quarter muffins and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 32 quarters.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Add all ingredients and stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: crisco icing(for birthday cakes)
directions: Mix well.
If color is needed, use paste food coloring only.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in oven to get hot (about 5 to 7 minutes).

title: old fashioned berry fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix egg and milk and combine with dry ingredients.
Stir in melted oil and berries.
Dough will be very moist.
Drop by spoonful into hot deep fat until golden brown.
Drop on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coconut marshmallows
directions: Toast the coconut until it is light brown.
Soften the gelatin in cold water in the top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water and stir unti the gelatin is dissolved.
Add sugar and stir until it is dissolved.
Remove it from heat.
Pour the syrup into a large bowl and add the vanilla and gelatin mixture.
Beat on highest speed with a mixer until marshmallow consistency, about 15 minutes.
Grease a 7 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Put coconut in the bottom of the pan.
Pour the marshmallow over it and cool.
Cut into squares and roll in coconut until all sides are covered.

title: broccoli casserole no. 3
directions: Cook
broccoli
as directed on package.
Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: Soak bran in buttermilk 15 or 20 minutes.
Mix flour with soda.
In another bowl, cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat slightly after each addition.
Add vanilla. Alternately add flour and buttermilk mixture.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Keeps 6 weeks.

title: cheesy chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken in 3 quarts water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Debone and skin chicken, cut chicken in bite-size pieces and set aside.
Add all remaining ingredients, except Velveeta, to broth; simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add chicken and Velveeta.
Let Velveeta melt.
(You can add more water to vegetables to get desired consistency.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and bake, covered, in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: chili sauce for one
directions: Bring chilies and tomato to a boil in top of double boiler. Add cheese and salt.
Heat, stirring, until cheese is melted. Serve as dip or sauce over vegetables or macaroni.

title: devonshire cream fruit
directions: In a small saucepan combine gelatin and 1/2 cup cold water; let stand 5 minutes.
Heat and stir over medium heat to dissolve gelatin.
Cool.
In a medium bowl beat cream, the 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla on medium-low speed until soft peaks form (tips curl). Combine gelatin and sour cream.
Fold into whipped cream.
Chill 1 hour.

title: banana-graham ice cream
directions: Break graham crackers into 1-inch pieces. Fold crackers and banana slices into ice cream. Freeze until firm. Top each serving with a cherry. I often set the ice cream to melt during our meal and quickly mix the ingredients after eating. Serves 6 to 8. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: banana boats
directions: Peel back a long strip of banana peel on the inside of curve, leaving one end attached to the banana.
Scoop out some of the banana and fill with marshmallow, chocolate, or anything you would like.
Be creative.
Replace the strip of peeling and wrap in foil. Bake in the embers (about 15-20 minutes) until banana, chocolate and marshmallows are melted and blended.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cake mix, sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.
Serves 12 to 16 persons.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Drain peaches.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons liquid from peaches.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Set aside.

title: strawberry torte flan
directions: Bake cake in flan pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread on cake.
Warm strawberry glaze and mix fresh strawberries in glaze; pour over cake.

title: quiche avon
directions: Mix eggs, cream, salt, mustard and nutmeg.
Add onion and cheese. Pour into baked shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Dump pineapple and pie filling in bottom of oblong pan.
Smooth out and sprinkle cake mix over evenly. Pour on melted butter, then pecans and coconut.
Bake for 1 hour. Serve in pan.

title: date cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add Cool Whip when you serve.

title: fresh peach trifle
directions: Sprinkle dry peach gelatin over sliced peaches.
Mix and pour into a trifle bowl (or clear glass bowl).
Place cubed pound cake over peaches.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve in punch cups.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter until clear and soft.
Stir in flour and mix thoroughly.
Remove from stove and stir in cream until smooth.
Return to stove and cook over medium heat until thickened (add milk if too thick).
Add shrimp, cheese, pimento, mustard, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Stir until cheese is melted but do not boil.
Spoon over potatoes (6).

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Beat egg and add sugar, vinegar, bacon drippings and salt. Bring to a full boil; let cool and then chill.
Serve over spinach leaves, topped with purple onions and chopped bacon.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend together soup, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir spinach, water chestnuts and onions into creamy mixture.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first seven ingredients; mix with beater. Add remaining ingredients.
Make into walnut size balls.
Press down and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place lettuce and cauliflower in a bowl (cut up).
Top with the mayonnaise, onion, sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon. Cover and toss before serving.

title: smithfield special
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef and diced onion.
Drain off any grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and pizza sauce to cooked ground beef and heat.
Place the drained macaroni in large oblong pan.
Pour beef mixture evenly over the top.
Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top and place in oven just until the cheese melts.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off grease.
Steam frozen vegetables until done.
Drain off water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix ground beef, vegetable with 1 can of soup; add 2/3 can of water.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with American cheese and top with mashed potatoes or Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Chop eggs and water chestnuts.
Mix first 9 ingredients together and place in flat baking dish, 10 x 14-inch.
Top with almonds, Cheddar cheese and potato chips.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: clam chowder
directions: Bring to boil and simmer a few minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes with maple syrup
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Peel the sweet potatoes.
Cut into fourths or eighths, depending if sweet potatoes are too large.
Brown well on all sides in a heavy skillet in the butter, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Don't burn.
Potatoes do not have to be fully cooked at this stage.
Add more butter if necessary to prevent sticking. Arrange potatoes in a casserole that has a lid.
Mix the sugar, maple syrup, juice, bourbon and zest.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake 20 minutes, basting often.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Rub mixture all over roast. In the bacon grease, brown roast on all sides in a large Dutch oven.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 3 hours.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening, add the milk and beaten egg.
Cover with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake in a shallow pan in hot oven at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: tilarney(serves 8)
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in small amount of fat; set aside. Cook macaroni in tomato juice until tender; add hamburg, corn and olives, mixing well.
Place in casserole; cover with cheese.
Bake at 350°
for about 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: jared's grilled jalapenos
directions: Split jalapenos in halves (length way). Scrape out seeds. Fill jalapeno halves with cream cheese.
Wrap with bacon strips. Grill on open flame until bacon is cooked. Cream cheese may also be replaced with Mozzarella. For the more daring, leave in the seeds. Mucho calente!

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, 1/4 cup milk, salt and pepper; make 1-inch meatballs.
In large saucepan, combine garlic, paste, wine, water, bay leaf, oregano, thyme and meatballs.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add celery; simmer for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon parsley.

title: fried rice
directions: Beat egg; add a little salt.
Heat a little oil in frying pan. Spread beaten egg thinly and fry.
Slice into thin strips; set aside.
Saute garlic until brown in oil.
Add onion.
When wilted, add pork.
Stir 3 minutes.
Season with salt and vetsin. Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in rice and egg strips; mix well.
Fry for 10 minutes.
Serve hot, garnished with chopped spring onions.

title: margarella
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onions, green and red peppers and mushrooms. Cook until onions are transparent.
Mix tomato soup and cream, then stir into onion mixture.
Bring to a boil; cook a couple of minutes.
Drain tuna; break into chunks and add.
Add chutney last.
Taste to correct seasonings.
Serve over wild rice or fried noodles.

title: orange pecan muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs and yogurt.
Combine flour and baking soda and stir into the creamed mixture just until blended.
Fold in nuts and orange peel.
Place liners in muffin cups and fill each 3/4 full with mixture.

title: barbecue bourbon wieners
directions: Simmer all ingredients except
wieners for 2 to 3 hours with lid on.
Cut wieners into
bite size pieces and simmer in sauce. Serve on toothpicks with crackers, if desired.

title: chicken bianca
directions: Fry chicken in olive oil about 10 minutes.
Add onions; continue frying until chicken starts to brown.
Add oregano, salt and pepper; continue frying until chicken and onions are well browned.
Add white wine; simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add a little water to make sauce.
Serve with salad, potato and vegetable.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Season and brown meat in skillet; drain.
Cook rice (1 cup rice-2 cups water).
Bring to boil, turn to low, cover and cook 20 minutes; do not rinse.
Mix soup, mushrooms and vegetables together with meat and rice.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with noodles and bake at 350° until bubbly. Do not cook vegetables before mixing.

title: pretzel chicken
directions: Take 1 bag of pretzels, run through blender to prepare pretzel crumbs.
Unused crumbs can be saved in the freezer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and beat all until blended.
Add in order pineapple, grapes, cherries, strawberries and bananas.
You can also add any other types of fruit you like.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, milk, egg, onion, salt, pepper and cheese and place in greased 10 x 6-inch glass casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter or margarine and blend until well coated.
Sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients at low speed for 5 minutes.
Increase to high speed and beat 10 to 12 minutes more. (Watch it grow!)
Put in graham cracker shell and freeze overnight.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve with raw vegetables.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat into the eggs the sugar, milk and nutmeg.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Put bread cubes into dish and pour egg mixture over bread.
Let stand until bread is thoroughly soaked. Mix in the raisins.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: hot hamburg dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in top of double boiler until cheese melts.
Best made day before.
Serve hot in chafing dish with crackers or Doritos.

title: never fail buttermilk rolls
directions: Add yeast to water, then other ingredients. Now add 5 to 6 cups plain flour. Let rise until double in size. Make into any shape roll you desire. Let set 10 minutes in warm place. Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into a ball. Roll in paprika and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs; gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by teaspoons 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir together egg yolks, milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Beat the egg whites until thick, add 1/3 cup sugar and continue to beat until smooth.
Place on top of pie filling and brown in 325° oven until golden brown.

title: orange glazed pecans
directions: Combine sugar and orange juice in a large saucepan. Cook to soft-ball stage (236° to 240°). Remove from heat. Add orange rind and pecans. Stir with wooden spoon until mixture become cream color (about 5 to 7 minutes). Pour onto waxed paper. When cool enough to handle, break apart.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in blender on chop, then on blend until smooth.
Put in jars and keep in refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream: oil, sugar and eggs together - Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the sifted ingredients to the sugar mixture, then add carrots and chopped nuts.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour or until cake springs back when touched.

title: fresh peach or strawberry sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, mix crushed fruit, sugar and orange juice.
Place over high heat and stir until boiling.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer until thick.
Remove from heat, stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Makes 2 cups.

title: red lobster garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, buttermilk and cheese until soft dough forms. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°, until golden brown.
Combine butter and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: cheesy sausage nachos
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink, drain well. Add 2 cups tomatoes and picante sauce. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered for 20 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.

title: sweet potato angel biscuits
directions: Wash sweet potatoes; bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done. Let potatoes cool to touch; peel and mash. Set aside 3 cups and keep warm. Combine yeast and warm water in a 2-cup liquid measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender or fork until mixture is crumbly. Add yeast mixture and warm sweet potatoes, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a floured surface. Cut into biscuits and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked asparagus royal
directions: Place a layer of cooked asparagus pieces in bottom of a casserole.
Cover with a layer of crushed potato chips and a layer of sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Cover with grated cheese and repeat. Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Mix soup, milk and cheese together and pour over cauliflower. Have crumbs well mixed with 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Sprinkle over cauliflower mixture.
Place in 400° oven about 10 minutes to brown.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions. Soften cream cheese.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Beat cheese and pudding together. Stir in pineapple and 1/2 cup coconut. Spread mixture over cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip over all. Sprinkle the rest of coconut over all.
