Decorate with the cherries and nuts.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in lightly salted boiling water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Add the green beans for the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients (wooden spoon is good).
Spread (not too heavily) on English muffins.
You can freeze these, but thaw at room temperature (before broiling).
Cut each muffin in 4 pieces. Broil until cheese melts.

title: tasty asparagus casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Blend in milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese and allow to melt.
Add soup.
Combine in layers.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: deviled short ribs
directions: About 3 hours before serving:
In large Dutch oven over medium heat in hot 1/4 cup salad oil, brown short ribs well.
Stir remaining ingredients and 1 1/2 cups water in and around short ribs. Cover pan and cook over low heat about 2 1/2 hours or until ribs are fork-tender.
Remove ribs to heated platter.
Skim off fat from remaining gravy.
Serve gravy.
This is excellent with mashed potatoes or egg noodles.

title: baked beans
directions: Look over beans, checking for bad ones and small pebbles. Wash in cold water.
Soak beans in enough cold water to cover them well for several hours.

title: cream cheese cups
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Put vanilla wafers in baking cups.
Fill with mixture (half full).
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool 1 hour at room temperature. Chill 3 hours in refrigerator.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add salt, eggs, flour and shortening.
Mix as bread.
Grease ball of dough.
Cover and let rise 2 hours.
Shape dough into small buns.
Place in greased baking pan.
Let rise again, 2 hours or more.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peach sweet potato puffs
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water 25 to 30 minutes or until tender; drain.
Let cool to touch.
Peel, mash and measure 2 cups potatoes.
Combine sweet potatoes and the next 5 ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pipe or spoon potato mixture onto peach halves.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers in salted water for 5 minutes.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stuff in peppers.
Put excess filling around edge.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 c. evaporated milk over low heat. Meanwhile, mix cake mix, 1/3 c. evaporated milk and melted butter. Press 1/2 mixture into bottom of greased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on cake. Cover with melted caramels.
Use remaining cake mix and drop by tablespoons over caramel.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: african greens
directions: Fry bacon and chicken wings until brown; remove and drain. Put greens in seasoned oil from meats.
Put in onion; place bacon, etc. on top of greens and cook for 1 hour.
Mix other ingredients together; stir.
Pour over greens and mix.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet heavily.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in 3-quart casserole.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High (100%) until lite brown (5 minutes and stir, 5 minutes and stir, 2 minutes).
Add margarine and coconut (optional) and soda.
It will be foamy.
Spread quickly onto greased baking sheet.
Spread as thin as possible for brittle candy.
Makes about a pound.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put ingredients into bowl, including pineapple with all the juice.
Mix together.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool, then top with powdered sugar.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Whip cream and fold into pudding. Line bottom and sides of bowl with vanilla wafers.
Layer pudding, bananas, wafers, pudding, etc.
Top with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: hot cheese squares
directions: Mix together and bake in medium baking pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco; add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 80 minutes at 325°.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix tuna, mayonnaise, onion flakes and relish.
Boil eggs; chop and
mix with other ingredients.
Put on lettuce or bread.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Mix everything but bacon. Place in a 9 x 13 pan, then layer bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream
the
first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla. Put baking
soda
in
water.
Add alternately with the flour. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine and cook together the shortening, sugar, molasses and egg, just until blended.
Remove from heat.
Add the remaining ingredients; cool.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° until cracks form on the top.
Do not overbake (approximately 7 to 10 minutes).

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix together ingredients and bake in a buttered loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
This dish has a very good flavor and no one can guess that it is tuna!

title: wacky cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, salt, peanut butter and milk.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute, if you don't, they won't set up.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed and set side to cool.

title: spiced cider
directions: Completely dissolve the sugar and orange juice in the cider before pouring it into an electric coffeepot.
Put spices in the basket and perk.
Serves 30.

title: potato salad
directions: Finely chop bell pepper, eggs and onion.
Add to finely smashed potatoes; stir until smooth.
Add the sweet pickle relish and the eggs.
Stir, adding salt, pepper and Season-All.
Makes enough for 10 servings.

title: strawberry-banana gelatin salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set.
Set the remaining gelatin mixture aside.
Combine the sour cream, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Spread over the chilled gelatin.
Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over top.
Chill overnight.

title: the salad
directions: Mix vegetables with enough dressing to coat.
Chill and serve with grilled entree and French bread.
Great the next day.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs and add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and add all but zucchini; set aside.
Wash and grate unpeeled zucchini.
Stir it into mixture.
Beat well.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix together.
Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour in 8-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter.
Combine all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with nuts. Chill.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or breadsticks.
Yields 4 cups.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a bowl whisk milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add sour cream, mix well.
Fold in 1 1/2 c. whipped topping.
Place half of the banana slices in the crust. Top with half of the pudding mixture, repeat layers.
Spread with remaining whipped topping.	Refrigerate for 4-6 hours before serving.
(Pie will be soft set.)
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sausage-stuffed mushroom
directions: Remove stems and chop.
Cook sausage in oil until brown. Remove and drain, keeping 2 tablespoons of oil in pan.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, cheese and crumbs.
Mix well.
Fill caps with mixture and place in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: cheeseburger lasagna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook lasagna according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, brown your hamburger; drain excess fat.
Add 3/4 of the can of sauce from package and cheese; mix well.

title: carpet cleaner
directions: Mix all together.
Apply with a clean rag, using only amount needed.
Be careful not to soak carpet through.
Always absorb excess liquid with a clean rag.
(I use this in my shampooer, as well.)

title: beef stroganoff supreme
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Drain.
Add onion soup mix and mushrooms.
Top with noodles.
Pour in hot water, moistening noodles thoroughly.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 20 minutes.
Mix flour into sour cream.
Fold into meat mixture.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening, brown sugar and salt.
Set aside 1 cup for crumbs.
Mix liquid ingredients and add to flour mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and place 2/3 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan; pat down firmly.
Mix together the last 4 ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick.
Spread on top of first mixture.
Put remaining crumb mixture on top.
Tap down lightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and then cut into squares.

title: shrimp amandine
directions: Marinate shrimp in olive oil and lemon juice about 2 hours. Remove shrimp; reserve sauce.
Saute shrimp in butter and garlic until pink.
Remove garlic; place shrimp on warm platter and add almonds and reserved marinade to butter in skillet.
Add hot sauce and vermouth.
Let simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over hot shrimp. Serve over rice mounds.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine
pineapple
and
cheese.
Mix
flour and sugar. Stir together.
Put in casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine.	Sprinkle
over top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Good served with ham.

title: chocolate cheese dessert is delicious
directions: Mix together with a fork and press into a glass 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until done and then cool completely.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients all together and fold in poppy seed.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut and country ribs
directions: Brown ribs and place in Dutch oven or roaster.
Cover with remaining ingredients and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
About 45 minutes before the kraut and ribs are done, add 6 to 7 balls of bread stuffing on top of the kraut and ribs and bake, covered, the remaining 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach & artichoke casserole
directions: If frozen artichokes are used, cook according to directions. Do not overcook.
Drain the artichokes and place them on bottom of a 3 quart casserole.
Squeeze as much moisture as possible from spinach and layer it on top of the artichokes.
With an electric mixer, blend the cream cheese, mayonnaise and butter or oil until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk and spread this mixture over the top of the spinach.
Sprinkle with pepper and cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until the top is lightly browned.
You can refrigerate this dish after putting it together.
If it is chilled, may take a slightly increased baking time.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Pat in bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, mix together with an electric mixer the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake in oven 40 minutes at 350°.

title: clam dip
directions: Add clam juice for consistency desired and mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Best if made several days before use.

title: tony's moo moo
directions: Add cracker crumbs and softened butter.
Mix in another bowl, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in another bowl Dream Whip and milk; beat until real stiff.
Then mix cream cheese and sugar mixture in whipped cream mixture.
Beat good.
Use a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Use 1/2 of cracker crumbs on bottom of pan.
Mold in the pan.
Use 1/2 of cream mixture.
Add 2 cans cherries.
Use 1/2 of cream mixture.
Put remainder of crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: volcano cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake.

title: smoked ham loaf
directions: Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot mustard relish
directions: Chop vegetables, then measure.
Mix all together with salt. Let stand 2 1/2 hours.
Do not drain.
Boil for 10 minutes, or until done.
Combine vinegar, sugar, flour, mustard and turmeric; let come to a boil.
Pour over vegetable mixture; mix well.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 15 pints.
Eat with meats.

title: brownies
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Pour oleo over top of Stove Top crumbs; stir.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of a cake pan.
Chunk zucchini and onions; put in pan with just enough water to boil.
Boil 5 minutes and drain. Stir in sour cream and soup.
After well blended, pour over Stove Top in cake pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a greased loaf or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the butter.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Spread frosting over top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle coconut over frosting.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Cream jello and cream cheese together.
Add water and blend. Add pineapple with juice.
When almost firm, fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: slow bake chuck roast(tender economy cut of beef)
directions: Trim away as much fat as possible. Slash remaining membranes. Pepper and lightly salt both sides. (No liquid, seasonings or tenderizer.) Sear both sides well atop stove. Put meat on rack in a roasting pan. Cover. Bake at 250° according to weight: 4 hours for 4 pounds, 7 hours for 7 pounds or more.

title: chocolate cinnamon brownies
directions: Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Set aside. Melt margarine and chocolate over low heat. Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla until thick and lemon colored. Add flour and chocolate mixture.
Beat with spoon until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's chocolate icebox pudding cake
directions: Melt German sweet chocolate bars with powdered sugar and water in double boiler over low heat.
Beat mixture by hand then allow to cool until thick (I place pan in sink filled with cool water to speed up thickening.)
When thickened, add egg yolks to mixture one at a time.	Beat egg whites to a froth and add to chocolate mixture.
Line loaf pan mold with a piece of wax paper and fill with half of ladyfingers, then chocolate mixture.
Repeat second layer.
Place in icebox until set (several hours) then top with whipped cream.

title: mexican green bean salad(diabetic recipe)
directions: Put drained beans in a large bowl. Add onion and mix well. Mix dry mustard and vinegar until completely dissolved. Add all other ingredients to vinegar and mustard; mix well.
Pour the liquid over the green beans and onion and cover the bowl.
Put in the refrigerator for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs and melted margarine.
Set aside about 1/2 cup crumbs to put on top.
Place remaining crumbs into 9 x 9-inch baking dish and press firmly.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine dates, soda and water; cool.
Cream margarine and add sugar gradually.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Blend in flour mixture.
Add in date mixture and nuts; mix well and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken stew
directions: Brown chicken and onions in a little butter and oil in large pot.
Add remaining ingredients except corn and limas.
Mix and simmer covered for 40 minutes.
Add corn and limas and simmer 20 minutes until limas are done.

title: frozen cherry salad(could be dessert.)
directions: Mix all together and freeze in long casserole dish. Cut into squares and can top with a pecan half.

title: ham and herb vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; beat until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until well chilled.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: stuard's corn bread
directions: Preheat skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Take pan from oven and add 2 strips of bacon to bottom of pan.
Pour mixture over bacon. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water for 8 minutes, drain. Add egg, milk, butter, onion and dry crumbs.
Place in greased casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add corn syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Nuts may be sprinkled over filling after pouring in crust, if desired.

title: french bread(easy)
directions: Add yeast to very warm water and mix well in large bowl.
Add salt and melted margarine or oil; mix.
Add (all at one time) 7 cups flour.
Mix well with spoon or by hand.
(Dough will be somewhat sticky.)
Place in greased bowl.
(Do not knead.)
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and divide into 2 portions. Roll into rectangle.
Starting at long side, roll up into loaf and tuck ends under.
Place on greased cookie sheet (sprinkled with cornmeal).
Let rise until doubled and brush tops with egg white mixture.
Bake at 450° until browned.

title: corn and green chili casserole
directions: Melt in double boiler or microwave, cheese, oleo, chilies and milk.
Add corn; mix well and put in casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven until bubbly.
Garnish with paprika or bread crumbs.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Stir ingredients together
and bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: salsa
directions: Saute onion in oil; add puree and spices and all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: honey chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and honey together.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Blend well. Add vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding,
marshmallows,
fruit cocktail and whipped topping.
Cherries must be	drained
to
point of almost wiped off to keep salad
from getting red tint.
Additional nuts are optional, but pudding mix already has some nuts in it.

title: granny goose cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine, egg and vanilla in bowl, beating until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake.
Beat cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Spoon over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yield:
15 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions.
In mixing bowl, mix coconut, sugar, sour cream and cream cheese.
Place filling between layers.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Mix melted butter and stuffing mix until well moistened. Place about half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan; pat down.

title: light beef kabobs
directions: Place steak and mushrooms in a casserole dish.
Pour teriyaki sauce over them and sprinkle with black pepper.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole, put layer of asparagus, layer of cheese and layer of broken crackers.
Repeat layering process.
Mix soup with half broth from canned asparagus and milk.
Pour over casserole and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and taco chips casserole
directions: Crush taco shells or chips.
Place layer of chips in bottom of greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle layer of chicken over chips. Pour several spoonfuls soup over chicken layer.
Sprinkle with layer of cheese.
Pour several spoonfuls of tomato and green chili mixture over cheese layer.
Repeat layering process until all ingredients are used.
Top casserole with additional grated cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Roll into balls, or cut with cookie cutters.
If using cookie cutters, refrigerate dough 1 hour.
Roll on wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown together ground meat and onion (chopped). Add soups, beans and tomatoes. Grease a large casserole dish. Shred half the tortillas and place in casserole. Spoon 1/2 the meat mixture over the tortillas. Slice half the cheese and layer over this. Repeat this process. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and water in 1 1/2 quart casserole; cover. Microwave on High 9 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are just about tender, stirring once.
Let stand covered.
Combine 1/4 cup margarine and soup in glass dish; microwave, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or hot and bubbly.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in cheeses, sour cream and onions; stir into potatoes; cover.
Microwave on High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Let stand covered.
Microwave 1 tablespoon margarine 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Mix in corn flake crumbs and paprika.
Sprinkle on potatoes just before serving.
This is optional.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp english muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut into wedges; about 4 wedges to each half of muffin.
Put under broiler for a couple of minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: daffodil dip(the lovejoy boys favorite vegetable dip)
directions: Wash the seeds and remove the strings.
Let the seeds soak in salted water overnight.
Drain well.
Then place the seeds in a low baking pan in a 300° oven for 20 minutes or until golden.
Eat with or without removing the shells.

title: oreo delight in a flowerpot
directions: Prepare desired flavor of pudding as directed on box, only using 3 cups of milk instead of 4 cups.
Fold pudding and Cool Whip together.
Crush Oreos and mix with softened butter.
Layer in flowerpot in the following order:
Oreos, pudding mixture, Oreos and pudding.
Put more Cool Whip on top and decorate with real flowers (stems wrapped in foil) or artificial flowers by sticking them in center of Cool Whip.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and butter by hand and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Spread this out in pan.
With a mixer mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour the ingredients mixed with mixer on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour this mixture over oats, vanilla and nuts or coconut. Mix well and drop on wax paper by spoonful.
Will harden as they cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pork chow mein
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil until tender.
Add pork, water and molasses.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts.
Heat through for 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add to pork mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over cooked rice and add chow mein noodles.

title: chicken jambaloga
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, stirring well. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Mix softened butter to both sugars; add to oats.
Add beaten eggs to oat mixture.
Mix in remaining dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tortellini carbonara with ham
directions: Place 3 quarts of water in a 4 1/2-quart soup pot or Dutch oven.
Cover, place over high heat and bring the water to a boil. Add tortellini and cook, according to the package instructions (5 to 6 minutes).
When pasta is done, drain well and set aside.

title: chocolate zucchini rum cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until fluffy.
With a spoon, stir in zucchini and rum.
Mix flour with nuts, chocolate chips, cocoa, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir flour mixture and milk into egg mixture until well blended.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add taco mix.
Next add refried beans.
Mix together.
Put in a deep dish.
Top with salsa, sour cream, and cheese.
(Put on peppers now if adding.)
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: hitching post hominy
directions: Brown meat with onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add drained chilies, hominy and soup.
Pour in greased baking dish. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash in half and scoop out seeds.
Place, cut side down, in a shallow baking pan containing a little water.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Mix butter, garlic and brown sugar together.
Remove squash and baste with butter mixture. Sprinkle with seasoning salt, pepper and paprika.
Return to oven, right side up, with water drained off.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes, until tender.

title: tarsha spann's macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	except shredded cheese, in bowl and spread
evenly
in	pan.
Spread shredded cheese over the top. Bake
at
350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(The more macaroni and the more ingredients, the longer it takes to cook.)

title: picante dip
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, just until sauce is smooth.
Serve with corn chips, tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender. Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cake cool and remove from pan; spread on the icing.

title: corn "oysters"
directions: Drain corn. Add well beaten eggs, seasonings and flour.
Mix well. Batter will be thin.
Heat oil medium to hot.
Drop spoonfuls in pan. Brown on both sides. Reduce heat and cook gently on both sides until center is cooked. Dust with powdered sugar or serve with meat course!

title: gumdrop bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt, then cooking oil, gumdrops and nuts; add to dry ingredients and mix until combined.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch baking pan or two small loaf pans; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done and cool.

title: girdle buster pie
directions: Combine crushed Oreos and 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Put into pie plate.
Put vanilla ice cream on top of crust and freeze. Combine Pet milk, cocoa, margarine and sugar.
Cook until like hot fudge.
Cool completely.
Put on top of ice cream and freeze. Top with 8 ounces of Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Store in freezer.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture slowly.
Stir in M&M's and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: Mix pudding and cook by directions.
Let cool.
Mix with other fruits.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice two bananas to mix just before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cut in Crisco thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Mix with spoon until all flour is moistened.
Cover and put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix shredded hash brown potatoes, chicken soup, sour cream and 1 cup Cheddar cheese together. In casserole dish in the bottom, put 1/4 cup of margarine and pour above ingredients in dish. Top with 1 cup Cheddar cheese and Corn Flakes. Sprinkle 1/4 cup margarine on top. Place in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken con queso
directions: Boil chicken until meat is no longer pink.
Drain and chop or tear into pieces.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, peppers, onions and blend together.
In 3-quart casserole, put 1/3 cup crushed chips on bottom.
Top with chicken, then 1/2 cup soup mixture. Repeat layers until all is gone.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: soup ala zucchini(serves 6)
directions: Place zucchini, potatoes, onion and garlic in a stainless steel soup kettle.
Dissolve chicken-style flavoring in 2 cups of distilled water and pour over the vegetables.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Puree the cooked vegetables, liquid stock, soy milk and herbs in a blender until smooth.
Return contents to soup kettle and heat until hot enough to serve.
Pour into bowls and garnish with chives.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, salt and milk together.
Cook on high until boiling, stirring constantly.
Turn to medium.
Cook until thermometer reaches hard ball, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; spread into 9 x 13 pan. Mix together and top with brown sugar, flour, melted oleo, coconut and pecans; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place a
layer of lettuce, a layer of onion and a layer of cauliflower
in bowl.
Put 1/2 of bacon (crumbled).
Repeat layers.
Cover
entire top of salad with Miracle Whip, sealing layers underneath.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Before serving, mix together.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything except the cheese in a large bowl.
Put in an oiled (with butter or olive oil) 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put cheese on top and bake uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into 1-inch cubes.
Soak overnight in salt water (at least 6 hours).
Drain and place in pan.
Cover with water; simmer until tender.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onions and bell pepper for 15 minutes, until tender.
Combine and add everything; blend together.
Grease baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese; return to the oven until cheese melts.

title: mushroom and potato chowder
directions: In a large kettle, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir to make a smooth paste.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 minute. Add the mushrooms, celery, potatoes and carrots. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add cream and Parmesan cheese; heat through.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: good old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend together the sugars and shortening.
Add to the eggs, oats, flour, baking soda, vanilla and raisins.
Mix together well. Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Leave on sheet for 1 minute to cool before removing.

title: sugar covered peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Add baking mix; mix well.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten criss-cross style with fork. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool.
Store tightly covered.
Enjoy!

title: potato boats
directions: Fix potatoes as for twice baked potatoes.
Mash potatoes. Beat in milk and sour cream.
Fold in other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fajitas
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and saute onions, peppers and raw meat. Stir-fry.
Add teriyaki sauce as you stir-fry, until vegetables are done.
Add meat mixture to warm flour tortillas (like a taco). Garnish with diced onions, tomatoes, sour cream and guacamole dip.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Stir German sweet chocolate in 1/4 cup water over low heat until melted and cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming well.
Add chocolate, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool and remove from pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Add rice and beans. Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and Fritos.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in dry covered container.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla. Gradually mix in flour.
Chill dough.
Roll 1/8-inch thick to cut out cookies.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add Kool-Aid, sugar and cold water.
Pour into Tupperware molds or other molds used for popsicles.
Freeze.
Eat and enjoy.

title: jake's peanut brittle
directions: Cook together the first 5 ingredients until peanuts are done, stirring frequently.
Do not burn.
Remove from stove.
Add the baking soda; stir in briefly just to mix.
Mixture should be poured onto a buttered sheet of Saran-type paper while it is still foaming; spread very quickly.
Takes about 30 inches of paper.
Do not kill the foam before pouring onto paper.
It must have some foaming action on the paper.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix brown sugar with melted butter; add vanilla.
One at a time, beat eggs into batter.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring Karo, salt, oleo and brown sugar to a boil.
Stir constantly for 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Add the baking soda. Pour over popped corn (and nuts).
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: tuna tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as labeled.
In saucepan,
stir	in rest of ingredients.
Pour over spaghetti in an
oven
dish.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until lightly golden.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil shortening, sugar, milk, cocoa, salt and vanilla for around 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and peanut butter and stir well.
(If you let mixture overcook it will turn hard too fast to drop on waxed paper.)
Drop on waxed paper and flatten into round cakes.

title: tim gump murphy pie
directions: You will need 55 gallon metal drum (wash toxic chemicals out), cord of firewood, outside fire pit or campfire, matches (10 packs), gasoline (2 gallons) and one garden shovel.

title: three bean salad
directions: Let set overnight.
Great to make ahead to take to dinners.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream butter with sugar and flour. Add eggs. Add persimmons, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Add buttermilk last. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut side pocket in chops and stuff.

title: sheet brownies
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a bowl.
In a saucepan bring to a boil butter, water and cocoa.
Remove from heat and add to flour and sugar mixture. Beat well.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Scramble sausage in skillet and cook until done.
Stir in rice and soup.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef until brown in frying pan on stove.
While cooking, add seasonings.
Prepare potatoes while meat is cooking (mashed potatoes).
In a 13 x 9-inch cooking dish, cover bottom with ground beef, then add cheese and put your potatoes on top of cheese.
Add cheese and spoonful of butter in each corner.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: "mock apple pie"
directions: Boil together the water, sugar and cream of tartar for four (4) minutes after coming to a boil.
Crush (not too fine) the crackers. Put into unbaked pie crust.
Pour the boiled liquid over crackers; add butter and cinnamon (or nutmeg) and put on top crust.

title: orange roughy in citrus sauce
directions: Place fish in shallow, nonmetal casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients, except marmalade and arrowroot, and mix to dissolve orange juice concentrate.
Reserve 1/2 cup for sauce.
Pour remaining mixture over fish.
Cover fish and marinate in refrigerator 45 minutes or longer, turning at least once.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients for filling.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Butter inside of buns.
Fill buns and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat with mixer on high until thick enough to spread.
It takes quite a while to beat.
Goes great on white or spice cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add eggs and pecans. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Be sure to bake the pie on a cookie sheet because it sometimes runs over.

title: macaroni and cheese(newfie style)
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Add milk, butter, salt, pepper and onion.
Add cheese, but reserve a little for the top.
Be sure to stir occasionally as cheese melts.
Add toasted bread that has been broken into bite size pieces.
Add tomatoes and stir gently. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: onion lovers! corn-on-the-cob
directions: Combine soup and water.
Spread on frozen corn.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish or on cooking grill.
Cover with waxed paper. Cook in range, covered, on full power for 10 to 11 minutes or until heated through and tender.
Enjoy to hearts content.

title: hush puppies
directions: Bring all ingredients except cornmeal to a boil.
Add cornmeal mix.
Add more if needed to make a stiff batter.
Mix well; will be thick.
Set aside to cool.
Spoon into deep fryer and cook until brown.
Makes approximately 24.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in large cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly. Arrange pineapple slices and cherries.
Pour filling over pineapple and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with wild rice
directions: Place bacon in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Place rice over bacon; reserve the package of seasonings.
Place chicken on rice, bone down.
Pour soup over chicken; top with package of seasoning. Add water.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350° or until rice is cooked but not dry.
Very easy and delicious!
Serves 4.

title: bonnie's simple sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, blending well. Divide dough in half.
Chill 1 hour.
While rolling out one half, keep the other chilled until you are ready to roll it.
On lightly floured surface, roll a little more than 1/8 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Frost with canned frosting or make your own.
Decorate and serve.

title: harvest apple cider
directions: Place cloves in a double thickness of cheesecloth; bring up corners of cloth and tie with kitchen string to form a bag.
Place remaining ingredients in a slow cooker; add spice bag.
Cover and cook on low for 2 hours or until cider reaches desired temperature.
Discard spice bag, cinnamon stick and tea bag before serving.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry onion and pepper in margarine. Add ground beef and sausage.
Fry until no longer red.
Cook pasta according to directions.
Mix all ingredients with sauces.
Put in one 9 x 13-inch or two 8 x 11-inch oblong Pyrex.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or until cheese melts.
Freezes well.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line 1 1/2-quart baking dish with one sheet of pie crust. Place chicken, onion, peas and carrots in dish.
Melt butter in saucepan and stir in flour.
Blend thoroughly.
Slowly add stock, salt and pepper, stirring until mixture thickens.
Pour sauce over chicken and vegetables.
Top with second pastry.
Prick top crust with a fork several times or with a knife.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together (will be lumpy).
Drop into hot oil and fry until lightly brown.
Drain well.
Serve immediately. Can be rewarmed in microwave.
Serve plain or with syrup.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil and cook over low heat about 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove soup bones.
Cut meat from bones and return to soup.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients with Dressing.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and minced onions to ground beef.
Mix thoroughly.
Set aside. Grease muffin pan.
Take biscuit (one at a time) and flatten out with your hand.
Place flattened biscuit over one muffin opening and loosely form on the muffin pan.
Take ground beef mixture and place in the center of the biscuit.
The biscuit will slide into muffin pan.
Sprinkle the top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cherries and nuts.
Form in 2 rolls (2-inches diameter and 8-inches long).
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or golden brown.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan.
In large bowl, beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add vanilla, eggs (one at a time), beating well after each. Combine flour, peels, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream, beating well after each.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: In greased shallow casserole, arrange layers as follows: 2/3 cup stuffing mix, green beans (partly cooked), almonds and turkey. Blend milk with soup and pour over.
Moisten 1 1/3 cup stuffing with water and butter.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox cinnamon rolls
directions: Add shortening and sugar to boiling water and let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in cool water; add to shortening mixture. Add eggs, vanilla, flour and salt and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, roll out in rectangles and spread with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Ice while hot with a thin confectioners sugar icing.

title: apple cake
directions: Toss cut apples, sugar and spice.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix egg, oil and vanilla.
Add this to first mixture.
Will be stiff.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: pineapple-cherry and almond quick bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl; stir well to blend.
Combine milk, oil and egg in small bowl.
Beat slightly.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in pineapple, cherries and almonds.
Spread in greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Let rest for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: quick spanish rice and meat
directions: Make Spanish rice according to directions, except use stewed tomatoes in place of tomato sauce and add meat.
When cooking is finished, top with grated cheese.

title: sliced fridge pickles
directions: Slice first 3 ingredients.
Stir vinegar, sugar and salt to dissolve.
Pour over cukes, peppers and onions and let stand out for 1/2 hour or so (cukes will sink).
Put into jars and refrigerate.

title: beef and bacon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Bake in a 1-quart casserole at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve with party rye bread or chips.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: christmas cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add mincemeat and chopped nuts.
Spray tube pan with corn oil spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter and press into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Saute sliced onions in 1/4 cup butter then pour onions over crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese over onions.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over the cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set like a custard.
Very good.

title: chicken salad
directions: In baking dish, combine ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Celery is supposed to be crisp.

title: green beans and mushrooms
directions: Saute garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in onions and set aside.
Steam or cook beans in small amount of water until tender-crisp; drain.
Combine beans and mushroom mixture; add pepper and dill weed.
Garnish with nuts.
Serve immediately.

title: dream dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake at 350° until done. Boil pineapple and sugar.
Pour mixture over cake.
Let cool. Mix pudding according to directions.
Put on cake.
Cover with Cool Whip
and as much coconut and nuts as desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: alaskan cookies
directions: In a heavy sauce pan, combine and cook sugar, milk, cocoa, and margarine.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
IMMEDIATELY add peanut butter, 3 c. mixture, and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to harden.
Store in a container in layers which are separated with wax paper.

title: oven fried pork chops
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine baking mix, paprika, seasoned salt and pepper.
Coat pork chops with mixture. Arrange in prepared baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes. Turn chops.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: sue's christmas punch
directions: Puree peeled bananas.
Combine all other ingredients (but ginger ale) with bananas.
Mix well and freeze until solid. Remove from freezer about 2 hours before time to serve.
Add 2 liters ginger ale now.
Serves 24 to 30.

title: salmon roll
directions: Mix together and shape into a log.
Roll log in chopped pecans.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: ol' doc's clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes a very good dip!!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine bay leaf and small amount of water in saucepan. Arrange zucchini and steam 8 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and next 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix.
Add zucchini, tomatoes and bacon.
Mix spoon mixture in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs and cheese over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Mix salad oil, sugar and eggs together and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured oblong cake pan.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy and gradually add sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well together.
Add rhubarb and pour over baked crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix everything together and make into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream margarine and 1 1/4 cup sugar together.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Mash 1/2 cup blueberries and stir into batter by hand.
Add rest of berries and mix by hand.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 10 minutes.
Take bread dough and let rise all day.
Flour your work area well.
Roll out dough to fit cookie sheet length.
First oil cookie sheet lightly then place dough on sheet.
Add Ragu to cover top, then put oregano, salt and pepper, then put Mozzarella cheese to cover top.
Place in oven for 20 minutes until done.
Makes 3 large pizzas.
Enjoy.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes and butter.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Fold into potato mixture and add coconut.

title: viennese jam cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Add flour gradually.
Shape dough into balls (2 teaspoons to each ball) and place on baking sheets. Flatten slightly and use thumb to make a depression in the center of each.
Fill these centers with 1/2 teaspoonful of jam.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Pour over melted butter.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be made ahead of time.
Serve with wild rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish tortillas
directions: Mix together and spread a little thicker than butter on flour tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate overnight.
(Cover with plastic wrap to keep moist.)
Cut in bite size pieces when ready to use.

title: banana meringue pie
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Beat egg yolks using fork; stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks. Immediately pour yolk mixture into remaining hot mixture, blending thoroughly.
Cook 2 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gently stir in vanilla.
Let mix cool while preparing meringue.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter or margarine in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Set aside.
Combine milk, flour and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture over the butter or margarine in the 9 x 12-inch dish.
Pour sliced peaches over the milk/flour/sugar mixture but do not stir them into the mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: baba's zabroshka
directions: To add flavoring and thickness to soups, lightly brown flour in a frying pan.
(Watch and stir flour; otherwise, it will get too brown and burn.)
Add a little cold water from the tap to the lightly-browned flour.
It will form a paste.
Add 1/4 cup of hot soup liquid to the paste, then put into the rest of soup and stir.

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of spring-form pan lightly.
Prepare a shallow graham cracker crust.
Pour cheese cake batter over top. In 10-inch spring-form pan, bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake in another pan with hot water in bottom.

title: house jogger chili
directions: In
a
wok or large frypan brown meat.
Drain
meat
of excess grease, then set meat aside.
Cut
up
all
vegetables. Thin slice
carrots diagonally about 1/4 inch
thick.
Put
3 tablespoons peanut oil in a wok or large Dutch oven or cooking pot.
Add
some
of
the cut up
vegetables
(green
peppers, onions, jalapeno peppers and carrots).
Stir-fry
or saute for approximately
10 minutes.
Keep stirring
during
this
time. Add remainder of vegetables, other ingredients and meat to the pan. Bring to a boil and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients. Add eggs and vanilla to mixture. Add flour and oatmeal again. Add raisins. Before baking, chill; shape into walnut-size balls. Bake at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: In hot oil, brown garlic, stir in shrimp for 1 minute, then add meat sauce.
Saute 3 minutes.
Push to one side of pan and stir in eggs until cooked, then stir in rice.
Season with soy sauce, m.s.g., salt, pepper and scallions.
Mix well.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a medium saucepan, combine the raisins, milk, lemon juice and peel; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and set aside.
Beat oleo, brown sugar and vanilla together until fluffy.
Add oatmeal, flour, walnuts, soda and salt; blend until evenly mixed and crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press the remaining mixture over bottom of pan.
Spread raisin mixture to within 1/2-inch of top. Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture, patting down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: surprise chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing. Put 1/2 stuffing mix into bottom of casserole dish, then, mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Layer chopped chicken, then soup mixture.
Add rest of stuffing mix and top with chicken broth. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Really great!

title: quick mini pizza
directions: Cut each muffin in half and toast in broiler.
Combine the tomato sauce, basil and oregano in small bowl.
Top each muffin with 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and any added toppings.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: debbie lackey's "chocolate chip cookies at their best"
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients with electric mixer.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Then add next 5 ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop a scant 1/4 cup of dough on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Space 3-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen large cookies. These are the best; our Cub Scouts love them!

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and vanilla with mixer.
Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Bake in a 9-inch round pan.
Do not frost.
(This is similar to a pound cake.)

title: creamy cucumber salad(this is a tasty salad!)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add vinegar and chill until partly thickened.
Fold in the remaining ingredients. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit fantasy
directions: Combine fruit.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons apple cider and toss.
Cover and chill.

title: italian shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp 7 minutes in salted water.
Peel and devein.
Pour Italian dressing over shrimp and marinate overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts, if desired.
Mix well.
Form into rolls and refrigerate for 3 to 6 hours.
Slice and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4 dozen.

title: apple 'n oat bread
directions: Combine apples, water and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Cook until apples are almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Cool while preparing remaining ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Stir in remaining brown sugar, oats, raisins and nuts.
Add apple mixture, eggs and shortening or oil to dry ingredients; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: better the next day soup
directions: Cook hamburger meat in soup size pan.
Drain.
Add onions to meat and all other ingredients.
Let all simmer 15 minutes.
Good served with sour cream and shredded cheddar cheese, cornbread or corn chips.

title: continental lemon sauce
directions: In small saucepan, whisk all ingredients together until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Do not let it come to a boil.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add	butter	and
sour
cream.
Beat a few minutes. Add chocolate.	Add
eggs,
one
at a time, vanilla and water. Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in 3 layers.

title: million dollar pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in brine strong enough to float an egg.
Let stand 2 weeks.
Rinse good.
Cut in 1-inch pieces and cover with fresh water with alum added.
Let stand overnight.
Remove.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat and chopped onions in large, heavy pan and drain. Sprinkle with salt.
Stir in chopped tomatoes until well blended. Add chili powder, oregano, flour, brown sugar, cumin and undrained kidney beans.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered, for flavor to blend.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: low calorie cheese cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until well blended and pour into crust. Refrigerate until firm.
Top with desired fruit before refrigerating.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until thawed.
Drain. Mix together all ingredients (except crackers).
Stir in broccoli.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: judy's homemade strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, oil and water together first, then add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Then add strawberries.
Mix for 2 minutes then pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain grease off.
Add 4 to 5 cups of water, seasonings and tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; 9 noodles for each pan (3 across and 3 deep).
In baking dish alternate a layer of noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and then Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese bubbles on top, in the middle.
Freezes very well. Makes 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans, 12 servings per pan.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Put the corn cobs in a kettle with enough water to cover and boil for 30 minutes. Strain through cheesecloth.
Measure 3 cups of the juice and put in a saucepan. Add the Sure-Jell.
Boil. Add sugar and boil for 2 minutes.
Skim off any foam.
Pour jelly into hot jars and seal.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: In a pitcher, whisk together sugar and water until sugar dissolves. Add lemon juice and stir. Pure the strawberries and strain to remove seeds. Add to lemon mixture and stir. Pour into glasses filled with ice. Makes 7 servings.

title: archie's chili(no meat)
directions: Saute green peppers and onion after slicing.
Mix tomato paste, crushed tomatoes and beans.
Add peppers and onion and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: low-fat corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, flour and sugar with Egg Beaters.
Stir in milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake in a pan of water until firm.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be doubled.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 2 eggs for topping.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture for topping.
Add baking powder, salt, egg yolks and milk to remainder of batter.
Beat for 3 minutes on low speed. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Spread in baking pan.
Arrange blueberries on top.
Sprinkle with reserved 3/4 cup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add the flavoring to the sweetened coconut; mix thoroughly.
Add the condensed milk; mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into the coconut mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove to a rack and cool.

title: clam-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt
butter
in saucepan.
Add garlic powder, oregano, bread crumbs
and bacon.	Drain clams, reserving liquid.	Add clams
to butter
mixture
along
with
6 tablespoons of clam liquid.
Mix thoroughly.
Fill
mushrooms
with	bread crumbs mixture. Sprinkle
with Parmesan cheese and top with paprika. Bake
in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.	Leftover filling can be frozen for future use.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a tube pan.
Glaze on top while hot with powdered sugar and Kahlua.

title: green beans, red peppers and potatoes
directions: Steam potatoes and green beans.
Place into a large serving bowl.
Boil peppers, peel and strip.
Add peppers and onions to potatoes and green beans.
In a jar, combine mustard, vinegar, oil and seasonings.
Shake well.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: pink salad
directions: Heat juice drained from pineapple and cottage cheese.
Whip the cream; add nuts.
Fold whipped cream mixture into pineapple mixture.
Pour into molds and chill.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place spareribs or back bones in 2-quart glass dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook with microwave for 30 minutes.
Rearrange ribs every 10 minutes. Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: ham glaze
directions: Combine ingredients and heat until smooth.
Pour over ham and bake for at least 1/2 hour at 300°.
Baste every now and then.

title: broiled mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Trim stems to 1/2-inch length.
Soak in cold water and lemon juice 5 minutes.
Drain and dry well.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil 6 inches from heat, until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Serve with remaining melted butter.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, drained mushrooms, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
Unroll 1 package crescent rolls and separate into triangles.
Place in a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate, pressing edges together to form a pie shell.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar together.
Stir in egg and molasses until well mixed.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Form dough into small balls.
Roll tops only in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and flour in a double boiler.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over crust and cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: butterscotch cookies(joe powell)
directions: Cream together brown sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla, then add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350°.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, oil and vinegar.
Beat in an electric mixer or with rotary beater.
Add onion and poppy seed last.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.
If it separates, beat again.
Especially good on fresh fruit.

title: panocha
directions: Combine sugars, milk, salt and syrup.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in water; set off the stove and let set 20 minutes.
Add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Beat until creamy.

title: quick oyster pie
directions: Spray a 1-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Put layers of crackers and oysters; dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Have layer of crackers on top.
When ready to bake, pour milk into mixture almost to top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and crackers are slightly browned.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until melted.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in a medium bowl, stirring well.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add flour; stir until blended.
Pour mixture into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until pie tests done (do not overbake).
Serve with ice cream and chocolate sauce, if desired.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and water. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: salad delight
directions: Stir jello in cottage cheese. Drain pineapple; stir in and add small marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes into a collander.
Add a pinch of salt and let drain well, pressing down with the hands to get out as much juice as possible.
Transfer pulp to a bowl.
Blend flour and sugar; mix lightly through tomatoes.
Add lemon juice.
Prepare crust for two-crust pie.
Pour mixture into pastry lined pie pan. Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust; slit top crust, seal and flute.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: noodles casserole
directions: Boil and drain noodles. Mix in a medium bowl all ingredients, then pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cousin suzy's apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over chopped apples and let "juice" for 20 minutes. (This is what gives this cake special flavor.) Mix all remaining ingredients together. Fold in apples and nuts. Bake in well-greased Bundt pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. (See High Altitude Baking.) Can freeze.

title: potato pizza
directions: Use desired amount of each ingredient.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in frying pan with enough oil to cook.
Add chopped pepperoni.
Cook until done.
Add pizza sauce and mix through.
Cook until bubbly.
Add cheese and heat until melted. Peppers, onions, mushrooms or other pizza toppings may be used to your liking.
Sausage should be cooked and drained.
Add with the sauce.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Hollow out
bread
pieces, leaving 1/2-inch thick wall. Spread interior with
1/4 cup of salad dressing. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup chopped parsley.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pack mixture into
bread.
Wrap in plastic.
Chill at least several hours.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Garnish with parsley.

title: scalloped celery
directions: Boil celery for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Then mix with almonds, chestnuts and mushrooms.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and cook until it bubbles.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk and chicken broth.
Cook until thick.
Blend celery mixture into sauce.
Bake in a casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 375° until hot and bubbly.

title: saucy chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, combine soups, sour cream, wine or broth, onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Arrange chicken on top of sauce.
Bake chicken and sauce over noodles or rice. Garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked tuna
directions: Cook enough noodles for casserole. Brown onion and pepper in margarine.
Add to noodles, soup and tuna fish.
Mix all together and put in buttered casserole.
Make hard bread with butter and season with salt and pepper; put on top.
Bake until brown.

title: sukiaki
directions: Heat skillet.
Add oil and meat; brown.
Add soy sauce, sugar and chicken broth.
Add vegetables, sliced thin.
Serve over rice. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: walnut fudge pie
directions: In small saucepan, combine evaporated milk, margarine and chocolate morsels.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; stir well until thick and smooth.
Cool slightly.
In small mixer bowl, combine eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed about 30 seconds.
Add cooled chocolate mixture and beat 30 seconds more; do not overmix. Stir in walnuts; pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until set and top is firm.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Crumble cornbread in large container.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Combine all to cornbread and mix.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown, but not dry.

title: leftover pizza
directions: Mix what you need into a soft dough.
Amounts depend on the size pan.
Spread
dough 1/4-inch thick in a pan, sheet or Dutch oven.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Use puffs from cream puff recipe.
Cut off tops and remove soft dough.
Fill with chicken salad filling.
Replace tops and refrigerate until serving.

title: seven-layer vegetable salad
directions: Layer vegetables in the order listed in a 2-quart bowl. Spread mayo evenly over top.
Sprinkle salad with remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Cover tightly and chill 8 hours.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat the whites very stiff.
When beaten, put in cream of tartar.
Sift sugar and flour alternately 5 times.
Fold in sugar first, then flour.
Bake in cold oven to start, set at 250°, for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: cream cheese and roasted pepper dip
directions: Put the pepper under a broiler and cook, turning often, until the skin is burned all over.
Put the pepper in a brown paper bag and close tightly to seal.
When cool, remove the pepper from the bag.
Peel it and cut it in half.
Discard the stem, inner membranes and seeds.
Cut the pepper into fine dice and set aside.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine Bisquick mix, cheese and poppy seeds.
Add to egg and milk and beat vigorously for one minute.
Turn into well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lima beans with sour cream
directions: Add all ingredients to hot lima beans.
Heat to boiling and serve.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, rice, water, 1/2 cup onions, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape tablespoonfuls into balls.
Put in pan. Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil; bake 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes.

title: broiled fish dijon
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Line cookie sheet or baking dish with foil.
For easy clean up, combine mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, mustard and pepper.
Spread fish with mixture.
Broil about 5 inches from source of heat for 4 to 8 minutes, or until fish flakes with fork.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Empty pie filling into serving bowl.
Add all other fruits.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine ingredients, except peanuts.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts; increase heat to high, stirring constantly until peanuts become light brown.
Remove from heat and quickly add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Spread thinly on greased shallow pan.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix in shortening; blend.
Add eggs, bananas, oatmeal and nuts.
Beat until thoroughly blended. Drop by teaspoonful about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cookies look done.
Remove from sheets immediately to cool.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage set at room temperature until soft.
Mix with Bisquick and cheese.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 450° for 10 minutes or until done.
Serve or place in freezer and warm as needed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Put yeast into a cup, add water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Stir and let stand about 5 minutes on top of oven.
Add cool milk, salt and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Sift flour in large bowl making a hole in the center, pour in softened yeast and milk.
After mixing dough, knead 10 minutes.
Place in large greased bowl, cover and put in pan of warm water, sit in warm place 15 minutes.
Put on floured board and knead 15 minutes.
Pinch off dough the size of a walnut.
Brush with butter, cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix drained vegetables and chopped vegetables; set aside. Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil; pour over the mixed vegetables.
Marinate overnight.
Makes 15 servings.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain the juices from the oranges and pineapple.
Heat to boiling point and remove from heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved. Cool and let partly set.
Add fruits, whipped topping and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix with your hand until it becomes real moist.
Roll into balls.

title: snowy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Mash potatoes in large bowl of electric mixer; add cream cheese, sour cream and salt.
Beat at high speed until smooth and light. Stir in chopped green onion.
Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish; sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter or margarine. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly golden brown and heated through.
This can be made ahead and refrigerated overnight before baking.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Wash beans; cut off ends.
Pack lengthwise in clean, hot pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headroom.
Add 1 clove garlic, 1 head of dill (or 1 teaspoon dill seed) and 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper to each pint jar.
Mix together in an enamel kettle the water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil and pour, boiling hot, over the beans in the jars.
Leave 1/4-inch of headroom.
Adjust the lids and process in a boiling water bath (212°) for 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.
It takes about 2 weeks for full flavor to develop.
(The added vinegar raises the naturally low acid beans to the strong acid category, so a boiling water bath is adequate for safe processing.)

title: corn salad
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Shred cabbage.
Cut up celery.
Grind onions and peppers on coarse grinder.
Cook slowly 20 minutes. This makes 7 pints.

title: ham and cheese omelet
directions: Combine eggs, salt,
pepper
and
milk; whisk until egg mixture is blended.
Heat an 8-inch Teflon skillet over medium heat until hot enough
to
sizzle a drop of water.
Add canola oil,
rotating pan to
coat
bottom
with
oil.
Pour
in
egg mixture.
As mixture starts to cook, gently lift omelet with a spatula and tilt
pan
so
uncooked
portion flows underneath. When done, sprinkle half
of
the omelet with the ham, cheese, onion and green
pepper.
Fold
omelet
in
half and carefully remove to serving plate.
Serves 1.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and onion until grayish in color.
Heat soups, enchilada sauce and milk.
Add to this mixture the green chili peppers.
Combine mixtures and pour 1/2 into a large casserole. Add a layer of taco flavored chips and top with a layer of grated Velveeta cheese.
Repeat process.
Place in 350° oven and cook until cheese is melted.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful scoops on waxed paper.
Work quickly.
Cool and eat.

title: russian fluff
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Fry hamburg.
In large frypan, layer raw potatoes, then corn, then hamburg.
Keep layering in this order.
Top with tomato juice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk 4 minutes.
Set off heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Beat and drop off spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until desired texture.

title: quick chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Mix 1/4 cup asparagus juice with soup. Place a layer of asparagus in baking dish, then layer of cheese, then soup.
Follow with Ritz crumbs.
Repeat the layers, ending with crumbs on top.
Pour the melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: macaroni cheese pizza
directions: Make the macaroni and cheese as directed, then bake at 375° for 10 minutes in greased pan; remove from oven.
Brown hamburg with the chili powder, salt, pepper and onion, then add tomato sauce. Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put chopped spinach into a medium bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Place in part loaf.
Use 1 round or oval loaf pumpernickel, rye, French or Italian bread (unsliced).
Cut a 3/4-inch thick slice off top of the loaf.
Using a knife, carefully remove most of the soft inside of loaf, leaving a 3/4-inch thick shell.
Cut scooped-out bread into pieces for dipping.
Fill loaf with dip, place on serving plate and surround with fresh vegetables and bread pieces.
Dip may be made ahead of time and placed in loaf just before serving.

title: delicious vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix together all ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Stir together.
Pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove and let cool to room temperature.

title: apricot or peach rosemary salsa
directions: In a bowl, stir apricots or peaches, avocado, tomato, lime or lemon peel, lime or lemon juice, green onion and rosemary. Cover and chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine beef, onion, celery, carrots, tomato juice, tapioca, sugar, salt, pepper and basil in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook in slow 300° oven 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and cook, uncovered, 1 hour longer.
Stir occasionally.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: strawberry carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup Bundt cake pan. Beat all ingredients, except strawberries and pecans, in large bowl on low speed for 45 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in strawberries and pecans; pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Prepare Strawberry Cream Cheese Glaze and spoon onto cake.
Refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with Cheddar cheese, cheese spread, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in chopped olives and shape into a ball.
Decorate with whole olives, cut into halves and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O (dry) with all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in buttered baking dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken & shrimp jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken in water seasoned with salt, pepper and bouillon.
Cut chicken in cubes.
Boil shrimp for 1 1/2 min. in chicken broth.
Add Old Bay Seasoning and bay leaves.
Remove shrimp.
Reserve broth.
In large iron pot brown onion, green pepper in margarine.
Add garlic, tomatoes and broth from chicken and shrimp.
Add rice; cover and cook slowly for 20-30 min. until rice is tender.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Heat but don't boil.

title: french toast
directions: Combine milk, egg and cinnamon together in bowl.
Soak bread on both sides.
Put in buttered skillet.
Cook on both sides.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Cook
green
beans
per
package directions.
Drain all water. Stir
cream of mushroom soup into beans.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter on low heat.
Add crumbs and mix until well blended.
Place
green
bean
