mixture in casserole dish.
Top with crumb mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbles.

title: seven layer bars
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, melt 1 stick of margarine minus 1 tablespoon.
Add cracker crumbs. Layer remaining ingredients.
Top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered with lid.
Stir occasionally.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef.
Add 2 cups cold water. Add flour and stir until flour is mixed.
Add chili powder, salt and beans.
Cook about 30 minutes on low heat.
Serve on rice or hot dogs.

title: black bean and corn salad (salsa)
directions: Combine beans, corn, onion, pepper and tomato in medium bowl and toss. Combine lemon juice, salt, coriander, cumin, black pepper and oil. Whisk together in a small bowl. Pour dressing over bean mixture and sprinkle with cilantro.
Toss to mix completely. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Save 2 or 3 tablespoons jello for rolling berries.
Mix all ingredients together and with fingers, form strawberries.
This should make about 2 dozen.
Leaves can be made with green cake icing.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix dry ingredients (sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed) and pour over vegetables.
Mix vinegar, oil and water and pour over vegetable mixture. Let sit for 4 hours or overnight.
Put in jars. Will save in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.

title: herb baked scallops(jimmy's harborside recipe)
directions: Place scallops in single layer in a large shallow baking dish.
Pour melted butter/margarine over scallops.
Sprinkle with parsley, basil and salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Stir to coat well with butter/margarine mixture.
Bake 20 minutes more or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: marcy's pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix well. Pour into loaf pan. Bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, on rack for remainder.

title: pink holiday salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk in a large bowl.
Chill 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk.
Gradually add meal to make a soft mush.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, sugar, salt and butter.
Beat egg whites and add.
Place in a greased Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.
Good!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour or until lightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Beat eggs, add brown sugar and pecans.
Put into tart crust. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until firm.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Layer in pan in order given above, then pour canned milk over top of layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes. Makes a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use 1/2 for a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: shrimp and cheese cold soup
directions: Put everything but the cheese, shrimp and pepper seasoning in 2-quart bowl.
Chill.
Two hours before serving, add shrimp and cheese.
Just before serving, add pepper seasoning to taste.

title: texas cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and baking soda. Boil oleo, water and cocoa. Add at once to flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and grind pears.
Combine pears, sugar and orange and cook to a thick syrup.
Add pineapple (and coconut) last 15 minutes of cooking.
Seal hot in sterilized jars.

title: salad gorgio
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain and mix cheese in with hands while pasta is still hot.
Cube or slice in strips the pepper, onions, olives and salami and mix well.
Add Italian dressing and mix together.

title: chicken in paradise
directions: Brown chicken well in oil.
Add garlic, salt and thyme.
Drain pineapple juice from can into skillet. Add wine, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving plates.
Stir sour cream into pan juices; add pineapple and green onions and heat through. Spoon over chicken and serve.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add water; mix well.
Add 1/3 of oil that has been heated.
Pour mixture in 9-inch skillet.
Dip oil from sides of mixture and put over top of bread.
Bake in one 9-inch skillet in 450° oven until brown.

title: souped up seafood(microwave)
directions: In skillet, blend
soup
mix,
water
and tomato paste. Add vegetables; top with fish.	Bring to boil.	Simmer covered 10 minutes, turning fish
once.
Remove
fish to platter; stir basil into skillet.
Arrange
vegetables around fish; top with sauce.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except lemon-lime drinks. Freeze.
Take out of freezer 1 or 2 hours ahead of serving time. Serve when slushy.
Add lemon-lime drinks before serving.
Serves 35.

title: debby's cake
directions: Blend the ingredients on low, then up the mixer to medium and mix until smooth. Pour into three 9-inch round pans. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onion and saute in oil in small saucepan.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Delicious on chicken, ribs and pork chops.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together, bake at 350° until brown.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Whip the cream.
Add milk and thawed lemonade.
Pour into shell and let stand about 8 hours in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon candy pickles
directions: Add lime to 8 1/2 cups water.
Add cucumbers and soak 24 hours.
Rinse 3 times to remove lime and leave in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine 1 cup vinegar, alum and food coloring. Add cucumbers and cover with water.
Simmer 1 hour.
While mixture is simmering, mix 3 cups vinegar, 3 cups water, 11 cups sugar, cinnamon sticks and red hots.
Boil until melted.
Pour over drained cucumbers and let stand 12 hours.
Heat to boiling.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: country chicken
directions: Cover chicken with water and boil until tender.
Cool and pull meat off bones.
Save broth; discard skin and bones.
Cook egg bow pasta.
Drain.
Cool.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oil Add mushrooms and canned tomatoes, parsley, and oregano.
Season with salt and pepper to taste; add a dash of red pepper flakes. Simmer.
Thicken 2 cups chicken broth with cornstarch.
Add to tomato mixture.
Grease a large casserole.
Layer in the following order:
Noodles, chicken pieces, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until "bubbly."
Can be frozen.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
Brown meat in oil in a Dutch oven. Cover meat with bouillon.
Add bay leaves, onion, thyme, garlic, allspice, parsley and wine if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for at least 2 hours or until meat is tender.
One hour before serving, add vegetables.

title: lemon basil pasta
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Return to pan.

title: pizza puff
directions: * Hamburger may be used instead of sausage.

title: turkey-vegetable pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cranberry float
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into glasses and top with scoop of sherbet.
Makes 15 cups.

title: mark's cookies
directions: Mix well the sugars with margarine; add eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir in soda with oats and mix well altogether. Add M&M's, chocolate chips and pecans and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage in large bowl.
Dice onions.
Add sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Put in a large jar and refrigerate. Will keep for weeks and is crisp and delicious.

title: corn bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: classic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream softened butter, sugars, vanilla, pudding and eggs. Add flour, soda and chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Toss all of the ingredients except Ramen noodles with dressing 1/2 to 1 hour before serving.

title: sugar free carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 9 X 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mom's deviled crabs
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery until soft, but not brown. Saute in margarine.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine sugar mixture, lemonade and Amaretto; stir well and freeze mixture overnight.
Break frozen mixture into chunks.
Scoop into glasses, filling 1/3 to 1/2 full.
Add carbonated beverage; stir until slushy.
Top each serving with a cherry.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips last.
Bake at 375° for 16 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
(Drop by teaspoonfuls.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil for one minute.
Let cool. Put berries into a baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, mix sugar and flour; stir real good.
Add milk, water and butter.
Cook on medium heat until hot.
Add well beaten egg yolks; stir in.
Cook until mixture is thick.
Add vanilla and stir.

title: toshi's favorite upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar. Arrange fruit, maraschino cherries and nuts.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour batter over fruit.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 20 minutes before turning over.

title: chocolate dream note cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix, 1 egg and 1/4 cup butter only! Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan, greased.
Spread mixture over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While cake is baking, beat 2 eggs and vanilla ice cream together until foamy.
After 10 minutes, pull cake from the oven and sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips over the top.
Pour ice cream and egg mixture over chocolate chips.
Bake another 30 to 35 minutes.
I use 7 minute frosting and drip chocolate syrup and cherries over the top.

title: hawaiian pineapple poke cake
directions: Bake the yellow cake and cool.
Poke holes all over cake with wooden spoon handle.
Spread the drained pineapple on cake. Combine the cream cheese and pudding with the milk; make pretty thin.
Spread on cake, then top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut or nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour or more before serving.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
On medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter; add the cocoa and then add the oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts with 1/4 onion and 2 stalks celery.
Tear apart; mix with soup, sour cream and wine.
Crunch Ritz in blender and mix with melted butter.
Cover casserole with cracker crumbs and sprinkle liberally with poppy seeds.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 glass pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter; spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, chopped pecans and coconut.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top should be a golden brown and bubbly around sides when bringing it out of oven; let cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Enjoy.

title: roasted garlic dip
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place garlic in a small roasting pan coated with the peanut oil.
Roast for 40 minutes, then let cool for 20 minutes.

title: crisp noodle chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in a single layer in casserole (9 x 13-inch).
In a bowl, combine soup, sour cream, soup mix and pepper; blend thoroughly.
Spread over chicken and sprinkle with noodles.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: mud pie cookies
directions: Melt oleo, add sugar and milk.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes. Add peanut butter, cocoa, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal.
When mixed well, drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet(s).
Let cool.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Measure out 1 cup of dry cake mix; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together remaining dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In the same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar; add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, gradually add milk, lemon juice and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes, or until center is firm.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon cherry pie filling over cheesecake.
Cover and chill 1 hour before serving. This cheesecake can be frozen with covering of foil.

title: veggie snack
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until browned; cool.
Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cut and serve.

title: rice balls
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and shape into balls.
Fry in hot oil until
golden
brown.
Add more bread crumbs if needed to shape balls.

title: bunch of fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease pan with shortening.
Sprinkle with flour.
In a large bowl, blend flour, sugar, powder, salt, oil, pineapple, vanilla, extract and eggs.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 70 to 80 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes.
Loosen edge of cake from pan. Cool on wire rack.
Cool completely. Glaze with Fruit Cake Glaze.

title: chicken salad
directions: Serve on lettuce with crackers.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cold water, vinegar and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots, crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad 2
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the 2 cups hot water.
Add sugar and stir. Add the next 4 ingredients that have been chopped to desired size.
Stir in the crushed pineapple.
Pour into prepared mold and chill until firm.
Unmold and enjoy.
Serves 6.

title: dolmathes(stuffed grape leaves)
directions: Mix meat with egg.
Add onion, rice, parsley, mint, olive oil and 1/4 cup of water.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Wash bottled grape leaves in warm water.
Gently separate. Place shiny side down and place one spoonful of meat mixture on leaf.
Begin rolling from the stem end of the leaf.
Roll, folding in the sides as you go.

title: lyle's sinful fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 12 (or larger) pan. Place in large mixing bowl the marshmallow cream, milk chocolate morsels and margarine.

In heavy large kettle, place sugar and evaporated milk. Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly; once it starts to boil, set timer and cook for 9 minutes. Pour hot ingredients over ingredients in the large mixing bowl and beat until well blended. Add vanilla and nuts, if desired. Pour into buttered pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Stir in onion, mushroom soup, water and rice (uncooked).
Skin and cut up boneless chicken breasts into pieces.
Press chicken pieces down into rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy topping for cobblers
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle over prepared cobbler instead of crust. This is very good on apple cobbler or peach.
Butter and cinnamon may be adjusted to personal taste.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: You will also need foil candy holders.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Mix crisp bacon bits with 1/2 cup Romano cheese.
In a 2 1/2-quart bowl, layer spinach, bacon cheese mix, mushrooms, onions and peas.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix flour, salt, egg white, Wesson oil and water. Stir in milk slowly.
Coat onion in batter and deep fry.

title: rudolph sandwiches
directions: Trim crusts off slices of bread.
Toast the bread and cut each slice into 4 small triangles.
Spread peanut butter on each triangle.
Decorate with raisins for eyes, 1 half cherry for a nose and straight pretzels for antlers.

title: golden wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over decorated ice ring in pretty punch bowl.
The color of this punch makes it a natural for serving at a Golden Anniversary Party.
Yields approximately 60 servings.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine noodles according to the pkg. directions, omitting salt.
Set aside, and keep warm.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix well in covered casserole or covered roaster.
Bake 6 hours at 250°.
Stir every 2 hours.
The last hour you can add cubed new potatoes.

title: jezebel dip
directions: Empty both jars of jelly and preserves into a sauce pan; heat until melted. Add horseradish; stir well. When completely mixed, pour into a bowl and chill. When chilled, place cream cheese on a platter and pour dip over cream cheese. Serve with crackers. Good over ham!

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and blend thoroughly. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: white chocolate - macadamian nut cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and egg. Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate.
Bake at 325 degrees on parchment paper until light brown. Makes 24 servings.

title: fat free, cholesterol free country herb dip
directions: In blender, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over cold milk.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add hot milk and process at low speed until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and process at high speed until blended.
Before serving, stir until smooth.
Serve with assorted crackers, bread sticks, cocktail breads or your favorite veggies.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: super stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and simmer over low heat with mushrooms until tender.
Add small amount of water to keep moist.
Add chicken soup; stir and simmer 15 minutes, then add mushroom soup and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Start boiling egg noodles.
Add sour cream to beef mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain noodles when cooked to desired doneness.
Ladle beef over top.
Serves 4 to 6. Serve with French bread and salad.

title: citrus salad
directions: Peel grapefruit and oranges, removing peeling and skin.
Mix all ingredients.
This keeps well for many days.
If pineapple in heavy syrup is used, sugar can be omitted.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Put in saucepan with water and lemon juice.
Cover tightly and simmer until tender.
Add sugar and cook a few minutes longer.
(If you want smooth applesauce, put through strainer.)

title: easy peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in a glass casserole dish. Add milk, sugar, flour and vanilla; stir together.
Pour into the oleo.
Pour peaches into mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake until top is brown.

title: world's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, honey and brown sugar until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; blend.
Add baking soda and flour; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes, until golden brown at 375°.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water to which you have added salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Remove chicken from stock, bone and cut up.
Save 1/2 cup stock.
Combine soups, tomatoes and chicken stock; mix well. In a casserole dish, make three layers in the following order: torn tortillas, chicken, tomato mixture, chopped onion and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well until nice and crumbly.
Add water, a little at a time, and toss with a fork until all crumbs are wet.
Press all together.
Roll out on waxed paper and flip into pie dish.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together in order given.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Cut up the chicken for frying.
In a heavy pot or electric skillet, melt butter and lard.
Add onions and simmer until brown. Add salt, paprika and vegetable stock.
When the ingredients are boiling, add the chicken.
Simmer, covered, until chicken is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir the flour into the sour cream. Stir it slowly into the chicken and cook, do not boil, about 5 minutes longer.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt butter. Add flour and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: party pretzel salad
directions: Cream butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add pretzels.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool.

title: celebrity caesar salad
directions: Rinse lettuce very well and pat dry.
Remove the tough outer leaves of the lettuce.
Pat dry and tear into bite-sized pieces. Put back in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: buckeyes
directions: By hand, mix first 5 ingredients well.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper; set aside.
In double boiler, melt chocolate bits on simmer until chocolate is fully melted.
Add wax.
When wax is completely melted and chocolate mixture shines, drop balls into the chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine the dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients to the dry.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts (optional).
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Line metal baking pan with foil, leaving about 8 inches extra on each side. Mix ingredients (except chicken) in the foil lined pan. Top with chicken. Sprinkle 1 pkg. dried onion soup mix over chicken. Pull the extra foil over the top and seal. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: chopped meat soup
directions: Brown hamburg with one
small onion, drain fat, add 1 (15 ounce) can tomato
sauce,
salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in 1 1/2 quarts
hot
water.
Dice
potato and add to mixture. Add 1/2 box
elbow
macaroni.
Cook
this
until
macaroni
is tender. Then add 1 can of peas or 1 can green beans, drained. Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare the eggplant and cut it into small even pieces.
Melt 2 Tablespoons of the table fat in a fry pan.
Brown green pepper and onion in the fat.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, and eggplant; simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Melt rest of fat and mix with bread cubes.
Spread over top of eggplant mixture.
Bake at 350°. (moderate oven) 20 minute or until eggplant is tender and bread cubes are brown.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef well.
Add seasoning mix.
Remove from heat and drain fat.
(Roll in paper towel.)
Mix together lettuce, tomatoes, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Separately, mix 2 parts of Russian dressing and 1 part French dressing, then pour over lettuce mixture and toss.
Right before serving, add crumbled cheese chips and toss entire mixture.

title: corn chowder with ham
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and celery and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Stir in creamed corn, potatoes, pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done, stirring occasionally.
Add ham and cook 2 to 3 minutes until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: yummy strawberry pie
directions: Blend together softened cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread into 2 baked pie crusts.
Mix together strawberries and glaze.
Spread over first layer.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: homemade vegie soup with chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts in 4 to 6 cups of water for 30 minutes. Remove chicken; set aside to cool.
Meanwhile, add vegies, tomato paste, tomatoes and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer until vegies are tender.
Add chicken taken off the bone and diced.
Simmer 30 to 50 minutes.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in crust.
Top with pie filling. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with 1/4 cup nuts and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix all together, put in refrigerator until firm.

title: absolute best new york cheese cake
directions: Melt butter.
In food processor or blender, put small amounts of sour cream, cottage cheese and butter.
Blend until smooth.
Add cream cheese.
Blend again.
Add eggs, one at a time, while blending in rest of ingredients (lemon juice, cornstarch and sugar).
Blend all together.
Spray a spring-form pan with Pam or grease it.
Pour batter into pan and bake on cookie sheet for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° until slightly brown on top.
Let cool for 2 hours in oven.
(If electric oven, door should be partially open.) Can serve plain or with fruit.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, and oil together until sugar is dissolved. Mix all together. Let marinate 24 hours, drain and serve. This keeps well.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together well margarine, peanut butter, eggs, sugars and syrup. Mix oatmeal and baking powder. Blend 2 mixes together.

title: garlic bread twists
directions: Spray a baking pan with spray coating; set aside.
Remove dough from package; do not unroll dough.
Cut pizza dough roll crosswise into 12 slices.
Unroll each slice into a rope.
Cut each rope in half crosswise.
Twist each rope.
Then place on baking sheet.

title: turkey and rice casserole
directions: Combine turkey or chicken and rice in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, saute onion, celery and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter for 8 minutes, stirring frequently, until tender and crisp.
Stir in soup, wine, mushrooms, sage, salt, thyme, pepper and pimentos. Pour mushroom-vegetable mixture in casserole.
Stir with a large spoon to combine.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.
If you use brown rice, cook covered 1 cup raw brown rice in 3 cups boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt about 40 minutes, or until water is absorbed.

title: chocolate egg nog
directions: Mix together and garnish with whipped cream and chocolate shavings.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine the oil, sugar, water and vanilla in a skillet. Let it get hot, then add the popcorn and cover. Shake continuously until the corn has popped. Pour onto waxed paper, cool and serve.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
In a medium bowl, stir the brown sugar, pecans, pudding, sugar and cinnamon.
Dip rolls in butter, then roll in sugar mixture.
Layer in prepared pan. Drizzle with butter and sugar mixture.
Cover loosely; chill in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Put on serving plate.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Scald first 6 ingredients.
Make sure it's free from lumps (put it through a sieve).
Add whole, milk, vanilla and maple. Makes 1 1/2 gallons ice cream.

title: lemon iced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let cool and serve.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour 1/2 milk over top.
Top with crumbs.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess squares
directions: Grease and flour 9x13 inch baking dish.
Mix first 3 ingredients and spread with a spatula in the bottom of baking dish.
Mix the next 4 ingredients, beating well and pour on top of cake mixture.
Spread evenly. Bake at 450 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Spray a large nonstick frying pan with nonfat cooking spray. Saute onion and garlic in chicken broth.
Add basil and other seasonings.
Add chicken and saute about 7 minutes until chicken is cooked.
Add zucchini and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add the fettuccine and milk.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and mix well. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: raspberry fruit ice
directions: Put pineapple in blender.
Add frozen fruit a little at a time and blend well.
Pour into 8 serving dishes.
Freeze 15 to 30 minutes.
Taste before freezing and add sugar if needed.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Place soups in saucepan.
Stir well.
Blend in half and half. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Chill about 5 hours for best results.
(Can be eaten right away.)

title: christmas gold fruit cake
directions: Beat butter until light and creamy.
Gradually add the sugar, beating until smooth.
Beat egg yolks together lightly and add to mixture.
Combine milk, brandy and vanilla.
Mix flour and salt together.
Alternately add milk mix and flour mix to butter mix. Fold in fruits and nuts.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Fold whites into batter gently, but thoroughly.
Pour mixture into two buttered and floured six-cup molds.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until they test done.
Cool and unmold.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients together with spoon.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: shipwreck
directions: In a greased casserole place a layer of sliced raw potatoes, chopped celery, hamburger and kidney beans.
Sprinkle top with bouillon cube, salt and pepper.
Dilute 1 can tomato soup and pour over all.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let chill until slightly thick.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill well before serving.

title: french bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening together; add yeast and water.
Mix until smooth.
Put in nine 1 pound loaves; let rise about 1 hour.
Roll out dough to form long loaves.
Put in loaf pans; let set for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; let rise again.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 9 loaves.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion and green peppers slowly in Crisco until onions are soft.
Add ground beef and saute until mixture falls apart.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Arrange in large covered dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
May add carrots.

title: keflins
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: topopos a la jalisciense
directions: Fry out whole, flat tortillas in a small amount of oil (the Mexicans use lard).
Drain off oil or grease.
Spread with refried beans, being careful not to break the tortilla toastada.
Keep warm in a 250° oven.
Mix lettuce and vegetables in a bowl large enough to have mixing or tossing room.
Mix oil and escabeche. Pour over vegetables. Toss well and allow to drain.
Pile about 1 cup of the marinated vegetable mixture on top of the bean tortilla.

Around the side, place 2 small or 1 large shrimp, the latter cut in half lengthwise, in each quarter of the veggie pile. In between, place two lengthwise wedges of avocado, lightly salted or dipped in the draining from the veggie mix.
Substitute the chicken or beef fajita pieces for the shrimp if you are using them.

Top with a slice of tomato and a ripe olive held in place on top of the tomato slice with a toothpick. Sprinkle grated cheese over all. Garnish with jalapeno peppers cut lengthwise in quarters and seeded.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine Bisquick, sausage and cheese; mix into a soft dough. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned,
about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Cook onion in margarine.
Add broccoli and cook until done.
Add soup and stir.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix with cooked rice and heat in oven until hot.

title: macaroni and cheese dinner
directions: Mix water and mustard in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Whisk in cheese from pouch.
Add macaroni.
Cover with a tight-fitting lid.
Bake 30 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crush into small pieces, enough pretzels to make 1 1/2 cups.
Melt margarine and mix with pretzels.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar, margarine and pretzels and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: turtles
directions: Melt margarine in 3 quart saucepan.
Add sugar and salt. Stir.
Blend in syrup.
Add milk and stir.
Heat mixture to 245° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into well buttered bowl.
Cool.

title: pasta-vegetable soup
directions: Combine 4 cups water and next 16 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes. Add remaining 2 cups water and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni and cook an additional 8 minutes; discard bay leaf. Ladle into soup bowls; top with cheese.
Yield: 17 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in order listed all ingredients except cheese.
Bake in greased casserole, covered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; add cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: caramel apple treats
directions: Mix apples, caramels, flour and seasonings in a bowl.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme.
Microwave, then spoon in tart shells.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Combine sugar, water and vinegar and boil for 5 to 10 minutes and cool. Add celery seed, celery and peppers to cabbage; mix well with sugar mixture.
Chill.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until like coarse meal.
Spread over bottom and half up sides of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange peach halves over crust and sprinkle with 1 cup sugar, mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; then pour a mixture of 1 1/2 cups milk and 2 eggs that have been blended together in a blender.
Bake for 30 minutes longer or until custard is done.

title: betty culver's spicy peach salad
directions: Drain peaches and reserve juice.
Chill.

Blend jello, sugar, cinnamon and cloves together very well, then add 1 cup boiling water, 2 tablespoons vinegar and reserved juice. Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, to keep spices off bottom. After mixture starts to thicken, add peaches.
Chill until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease angel food pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Mix butterscotch pudding and cinnamon in bowl.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Pour melted margarine over rolls.
Let sit out overnight.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle with icing.

title: cranberry tea bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter and sugar together until creamy; beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and cloves; add to creamed mixture and stir until well blended.
Mix in cranberry sauce, nuts and raisins.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and flour-dusted 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool bread in pans 10 minutes, then turn out on a wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: nacho hot dish
directions: Cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes in 8-inch square pan, stirring frequently.

title: white cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift and re-sift flour before measuring.
Mix flour, baking powder and milk into sugar and butter mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: moon cake
directions: Cream cheese; add milk, then pudding.
Pour this mixture over cake.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of jelly roll pan with rolls, pinching together at perforations.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing together.
Spread over this.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Boil egg noodles until tender and set aside, keeping warm. Finely chop bell pepper and onion.
Fry ground beef, onion, bell pepper and seasoned salt.
Drain excess fat.
Add soup and liquid to ground beef mixture.
Let cook through for about twenty minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve over noodles.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler; stir in milk. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cook, uncovered, 15 minutes more, stirring occasionally. Beat egg yolks. Gradually stir in hot mixture. Return to double boiler. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Line bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole with vanilla wafers. Top with a layer of sliced bananas. Pour a portion of custard over the bananas. Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard, ending with remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until mixture forms stiff peaks. Pile on top of pudding in casserole. Bake in preheated hot oven.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; add sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer. Add to shells.
Layer shells, then pepperoni and Mozzarella.
Top with Parmesan cheese and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugars and spices.
Stir in ice cream.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into plastic container with lid and freeze.
Mixture will keep in freezer for months!

title: zippy carrots
directions: *Real "zippy" if made with Freeman Reynolds' horseradish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and put in shallow pan.
Combine the rest of tomato sauce and all other ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: country cornbread
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients well. Bake in greased pan or muffin tin (makes 12) for 12 minutes or until brown at 475°.

title: cold beet soup
directions: In blender or food processor, combine beets, broth, onion, lemon, dill weed and salt to taste.
Process until all ingredients are pureed.
Pour into refrigerator container and stir in sour cream or yogurt.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve cold.
Garnish with fresh dill, parsley and/or thin cucumber slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Line large pizza pan with a double recipe of pie dough. A jelly
roll
pan
can
also be used.
Bake crust until light brown at 425°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and run them through a potato ricer into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except the marshmallows and whip with a mixer until light.
Place in a baking dish and top with the marshmallows.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until the marshmallows brown and the dish is hot.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinade overnight.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9-inch pan.
Mix the first 3 ingredients. Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add applesauce mixture to dry ingredients. Add the raisins and nuts.
Blend well and spoon into pan.
Bake about 40 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemonade concentrate and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in whipped topping and fold in fruit.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion.
Saute until onion is soft.
Set aside.

title: mother's best lima beans
directions: Cook beans to directions.
Reserve liquid and set aside. Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in butter; add flour and seasonings.
Stir until mixed in well, add cream and simmer. Fold in beans (if too dry, some of reserved liquid may be added). Serve.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper and butter chops lightly.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Slice onions and potatoes on top of chops.
Add mushroom soup.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook the chicken in a lot of water until done.
Put 4 1/2 cups of the broth in a large pan and bring to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes and onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Add the rice and cook 30 minutes on simmer.
Debone and cut up chicken.
Add chicken to rice when rice is done.
Mix well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon melting moments
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add extract, cornstarch and flour. Form into nickel-size balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until firm. Frost with icing made with 10x sugar and lemon juice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix together all ingredients and bake for 1 hour.
When done, butter top and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; seed. Scald in hot water 4 or 5 minutes; drain. Brown beef and onion in skillet. Add the rice, tomatoes, eggs and sour cream. Season to taste with salt and black pepper. Stuff pepper halves and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pepper is tender.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix well and make into a roll.
Let stand in icebox overnight. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade sauerkraut
directions: Will also need sterilized pint or quart jars.

title: dressing for green salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in refrigerator.

title: bran-apple muffins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat twelve 2 3/4-inch muffin tin cups with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine buttermilk, prune juice, bran, rolled oats and baking soda; set aside.
In the container of food processor, combine the prunes and water.
Pulse on and off until prunes are finely chopped.
Combine prune puree and sugar in a mixer bowl; beat in egg whites and molasses.
Stir in buttermilk mixture, flour, apple and salt; blend thoroughly.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin tin cups, dividing equally.
Sprinkle tops lightly with additional rolled oats.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour pans. Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla. Cream well. Sift 3 cups flour; add soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly. Add nuts and bake until done.

title: bread and butter pickles(green tomatoes or cucumbers)
directions: Choose smooth, even sized tomatoes that have acquired the whitish color which appears just before ripening or use fresh cucumbers; wash.
Remove stem end and blossom scar neatly, then cut into quarter-inch crosswise slices.
Put into enamelware or glass bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and add water.
Cover and let stand 24 hours.
Turn into a colander and let drain 10 to 15 minutes.
Now, put into a preserving kettle; add onions, peeled and sliced thinly, then vinegar, sugar and spices.
Heat to boiling; simmer 3 or 4 minutes.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash after cooking.
Add sugar, mayonnaise, egg and onion.
Pat in dish about 10 x 6-inches.
Top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Finally top with 1/2 stick oleo, melted. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar and vanilla; mix. Fold in Cool Whip. Line the crusts with banana slices. Pour the mixture over the bananas. Slice another layer of bananas on top. Spoon the blueberry pie filling on top of bananas, using 1/2 can each pie. Chill well and serve.

title: cornish pasty(old family recipe)
directions: Unfold and lay out 1 pie crust on a cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, combine stew meat, onions, potatoes and sage (sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste).
Potatoes should appear green with sage. If not, gradually add 1 teaspoon more at a time until they do. Pile mixture high onto center or pie crust.
Lay second pie crust over mixture.
Seal the 2 crusts together by folding bottom crust over top and press down.
Make a few small slits in top crust. Cook in 350° oven until juice runs freely from bottom of crust (about 1 hour) and crust is dark golden.

title: light and zesty chicken n' rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can onions around and under chicken.
Combine bouillon and Italian seasoning, pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
This is good with soy sauce.

title: green beans (barbecued)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Very good.

title: popovers
directions: Combine milk, flour, oil and salt.
Beat with an electric beater set on high speed for 1 minute.
Add eggs one at a time, beat 20 seconds after adding each egg.
Grease 8 muffin tins or custard cups.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Set in a cold oven.
Turn heat to 425°.
Bake 35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Remove from oven; let stand a few minutes, then remove from pan.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup; microwave at High 3 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; microwave at High 4 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet or unbuttered non-stick coated cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
By hand, mix ingredients together (except frosting).
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted, boiling water until tender; drain. Arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.

title: mexican fried chicken
directions: Roll chicken
in
mixture
of
flour
and chili powder. Brown chicken in hot fat.
Reduce heat; add other ingredients. Cover; simmer until done, about 40 minutes.

title: white fudge candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate, stirring in Eagle Brand milk as it starts to melt. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into long, buttered baking dish. Chill 3 hours. Cut into squares.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts. Spread into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: apple-cranberry casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish or 9-inch pie plate.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on Triscuits crackers.

title: philly-chili mexican dip
directions: Melt Philly and chili over medium heat until blended.
Serve hot with tortilla chips and salsa.
Now is that easy or what?

title: heavenly angel food dessert
directions: In a 13x9-inch baking dish, break angel food cake into chunks and cover bottom of dish.
Make vanilla pudding according to package directions.
When slightly thickened, pour over angel food cake.
Next layer cherry pie filling over pudding, then top with cool whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pancakes with orange sauce
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk, orange juice and margarine.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Bake 4 large pancakes on hot griddle, one at a time, using 2/3 cup batter for each.
Stack pancakes, spreading cottage cheese between each.
To serve, cut into wedges and spoon Orange Sauce over top.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve on crackers such as Ritz, etc.
Can be made into ball and rolled in additional chopped nuts.

title: breakfast granola
directions: Mix all ingredients together and toast in shallow baking pan tray for 1 hour at 325°, stirring mixture thoroughly every 15 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook the rice in lightly salted water according to package directions.
Cool slightly.
Mix with the next 8 ingredients for filling.

title: apple nobby cake
directions: Break eggs over apples and stir well with the oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mixture will be thick.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Stir in by hand, remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 60 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 2 hours before removing from pan.

title: miss nellie myer's pie (1949)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into flour and sugar.
Add vinegar and egg, mixing lightly to form dough.
Roll out and line a deep pie plate.
Flute edges.
Spread fruit over the bottom.
Beat egg yolks, sugar, flour, sour cream, milk, vanilla and salt together.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the egg mixture.
Pour over the fruit.
Bake 45 minutes; turn off oven and leave pie an additional 10 minutes.
Open oven door and leave in the oven a few minutes longer.

title: easy bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients; add flour slowly until you can't stir.
Then knead with hands until dough is nonsticky, but soft to the touch.
Let raise at least 1 hour.
Punch down and shape into desired form.
Raise and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to a soft ball.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until loses gloss.

title: easy rice and crawfish jambalaya
directions: Spray the bottom of your rice cooker very well with Pam or butter.
Mix well and cook in cooker the length of time required by your cooker.
You might have to cook longer, depending on how "wet" you like your rice.
You can also cook this on the top of your stove, the length of time it takes you to cook rice.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1/3 cup of juice.
Melt marshmallows in juice in top of double boiler.
Let cool, add 1 1/2 cups crushed pineapple.
Fold whipped cream into pineapple mixture.
Place in shell and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan; stir in brown sugar.
Place pineapple slices (4 on each side and 4 halves down center).
Put 1/2 of cherry in center of each ring.
Mix cake by directions on box, using reserved pineapple juice for water.
Add water if necessary.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes.
Invert on plate.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Mix together. Pour into greased 8 X 8 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: liddy's crispy chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
One-half hour before serving, spread both sides of chicken with marinade.
Put in pan. Broil, basting with pan juices.
Turn frequently until chicken is tender and quite brown, 30 to 45 minutes.
To cook on outdoor grill, double marinade and save half for basting.
Serves 4.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Stir the mixture, then fill to the 1/2 cup line with apple cider vinegar, then fill to the 1 cup line with ketchup.
Melt 1 stick margarine in saucepot.
Add seasoning and 1/2 cup water; simmer in saucepot until thick (about 5 minutes).
Stir constantly. The sauce stores in refrigerator.

title: hanky panks
directions: Brown sausage and beef; add red pepper flakes, oregano and garlic.
After thoroughly mixed, add cubed cheese and heat until well melted.
Spread on party rye.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
After frozen, place in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, place in oven (frozen) and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Cook veal and pork in water until done.
(Cook chicken until done, if used.)
Cook chopped onions and celery until done, then add next 4 ingredients and cook altogether about 20 minutes. Thicken with cornstarch or flour.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes a lovely meal.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix milk, sugar and Bisquick together.
Pour into casserole, then add peaches to top and bake for 45 minutes or until done in 350° oven.

title: russian salad
directions: Cool all vegetables, mix thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: cool sprite(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on low speed until smooth.

title: tang pies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together real well and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Let chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour half of cake batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat. Remove cake from oven and pour caramel mixture over cake. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour the remainder of the chocolate batter on top and return to the oven and bake for 20 minutes longer.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: country ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Heat oil and butter in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Brown ribs.
Add garlic and cook with ribs just until golden.
Remove ribs.
Saute red onion in drippings until tender.
Add caraway seed, sauerkraut, sweet red pepper, broth, salt and pepper to taste and brown sugar.
Bring to boil.
Remove from stove and top with apples and ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until pork is tender.
Stir in carrots last 10 minutes of baking. Adjust seasonings to taste.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in butter; simmer for 15 minutes. Pour into blender, small amount at a time; blend until smooth. Add chicken broth, cream, nutmeg and salt and pepper to taste. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: welsh cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in margarine until very fine.
Add currants and mix well.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Mix until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Roll to 3/8-inch thick and cut with 2-inch cutter.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat lightly in olive oil with garlic and onion; add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer covered 2 to 3 hours.
Cook noodles in salted boiling water until tender.
Drain noodles just before making.
In a shallow baking dish, put a layer of noodles and a layer of meat mixture and layer of each kind of cheese.
Repeat layers and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cold water. Add gelatin to soup.
Cool.
Beat together cheese and mayonnaise. Blend in soup mixture.
Add vegetables, shrimp and crab meat if using.
Fold into greased 1-quart mold.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Serve with crackers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add syrup, milk and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Do not stir again until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Do not stir.
Let cool 1/2 hour. Beat until stiff and pour into pan.

title: feathery light dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients, cut in shortening.
Add milk and egg. Drop by spoonful on top of boiling meat and juices (I use ham). Cover tightly and steam 12 minutes without removing cover.
Makes 6 fluffy dumplings.

title: holiday feta cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and feta cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add onion, pepper and walnuts; mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours or until chilled.
Shape into ball.
Roll in additional finely chopped walnuts or chopped fresh parsley, if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pineapple walnut cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and pineapple until well blended. Add flour and baking soda and walnuts.
Mix well.
Do not drain pineapple.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: In medium skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken, bouillon and garlic.
Stir-fry until chicken is browned.
Remove chicken, add remaining butter and next 6 ingredients.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Cover, cook just until broccoli is tender.
Stir in macaroni, chicken and peas.
Heat through. Blend milk into flour, stir into macaroni mixture.
Add cheese.
Cook, stirring gently, until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: After sauteing, blend the rest of the ingredients together and add to vegetable mixture.
Bring to a boil and then let simmer 45 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: roasted vegetable soup
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Place carrots, potatoes, parsnips, onions and garlic in medium roasting pan.
Sprinkle with oil, salt and pepper and toss to coat vegetables evenly; arrange vegetables in a single layer.
Place pan in oven and immediately lower oven temperature to 350°.
Roast vegetable, uncovered, for about 1 hour and 40 minutes, stirring several times, until tender and lightly browned.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, cheese spread and onion together.
Shape in balls and roll in pecans.

title: taffy
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until stringy.
Add vanilla. Cool and pull.

title: sausage noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Add both cans of soup and mushrooms.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Pour cooked and drained noodles along with prepared sauce into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together shortening, honey, molasses, egg and milk, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: collards
directions: Cut off and discard tough stems and discolored leaves from collards.
Wash greens thoroughly.
Combine ham hock and water in Dutch oven; bring to a boil and cook 15 to 30 minutes.
Add collards; cover and cook at low boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste with salt.

title: seafood mold
directions: Heat soup and gelatine about 1 minute.
After it begins to boil, remove from heat.
Add Philly and mayonnaise.
Fold in crabmeat and chopped vegetables.
Mix well.
Spray gelatin mold with nonstick spray. Pour mixed ingredients in mold.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers, low in fat or fat free.

title: chocolate italian cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Mix together flour, baking powder, cocoa, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to mixture a little at a time, alternating flour and milk.
Add vanilla and fold in walnuts and chips.

title: best cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together three times. Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add vanilla, pineapple and coconut.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chives galore yogurt topping
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve over baked Idaho potatoes.
Makes about 1 cup topping.
About 10 calories per tablespoon.

title: clams casino
directions: Open shells, letting clams remain in 1/2; throw away other half.
Arrange clams in a shallow baking pan.
On each clam put Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, bacon and breadcrumbs.
Broil 4 inches from broiler until edges of clams curl and bacon is done, probably 2 to 3 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain water chestnuts and slice thin.
Mix all together.
Put in 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Top with corn bread stuffing and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine first three ingredients, using a fork to cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add last 3 ingredients to mix and mix well.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 crusts.

title: scones from scotland
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine egg and milk.
Measure Bisquick into a bowl.
Add sugar, rind and raisins.
Add milk and stir with fork until soft dough is formed.
Knead 30 seconds on floured board.
Divide dough into equal parts or roll each into a circle, 1/2-inch thick.
With a sharp knife, cut each circle into 6 triangles.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with milk or slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in hot oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 scones.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken pieces; mix cut chicken with salad dressing, soup and eggs.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; top with broken potato chips.
Bake at 350° in 8-inch Pyrex for 40 minutes.

title: souper burger
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender (use shortening if necessary).
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat. Add soup and seasonings.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Serve on buns. Makes about 3 cups.

title: maui mango bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add 2 eggs one at a time.
With third egg, add vanilla and coconut extract.
Add half of the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir with spatula.
Add remaining flour, nuts and mangoes.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: raised donuts
directions: Let milk cool to lukewarm. Take 1/2 c. of the cooled milk and to this add 1 tsp sugar and 1/2 cake yeast. Add the rest of the milk. Then add sugar, shortening, eggs and salt which has been beaten together. Add 4 c. flour for soft dough. Fry in deep fat.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Combine everything in crock-pot. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: glorified peanuts
directions: Mix peanuts and sugar with 1 cup water in large skillet with 3 drops food coloring.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture crystallizes.
Spread on large greased cookie sheet, separating peanuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Cool in pan.
Break into pieces.
Store in covered container.

title: greek beef stew
directions: Brown the beef cubes on all sides in a skillet in 1/4 cup butter.
Transfer the meat to a casserole.
In the skillet, saute the onions until golden.
Transfer the onions to the casserole.
To the skillet add the tomato paste and water.
Bring the sauce to a boil and pour it over the meat and onions.
Cover the casserole and simmer the stew in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the carrots and potatoes, cinnamon, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover the casserole and cook for 30 to 35 minutes longer at 350°, until meat and vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
If using fresh chili, wash green chili but do not cut it.
Place whole chili on baking sheet and roast for about 15 minutes or until chili begins to soften.
Remove from oven, cool and slice the chili.
Discard the seeds.
Combine all the ingredients in a food processor or blender.
Process or blend just until all ingredients are finely chopped.
Do not puree. Chill and serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in a baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over rice.
Do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Chill.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Shape eggs.
Using toothpick, dip eggs into chocolate.

title: "mini" cheesecakes
directions: Use midget baking cups.
Mix ingredients together.
Put 1 vanilla wafer (top down) in each baking cup.
Pour in batter (approximately 1/2 to 3/4 full).
Place on cookie sheet or pan. Bake in oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and top with cherry or other pie filling.
Yields 30 to 40 cheesecakes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Simmer.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta cheese and eggs.
In large baking dish, spoon meat mixture to cover bottom of dish. Alternate layer of noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce, forming 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: jane's hot dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler, then pour in pepper-tomato sauce.
Pour in a serving dish with plenty of corn chips available.

title: chili dressing in a hurry
directions: Puree all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: english muffin crab bites
directions: Melt cheese and butter; stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Mix crabmeat, salt, garlic salt and mayonnaise. Combine with cheese and butter mixture.
Let stand until cool. Cut muffins in half.
Stir crab mixture to blend after cooling and spread onto muffin halves.	Cut into triangles and place on a cookie sheet.
Place in freezer (uncovered) for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheese straws
directions: Allow cheese and margarine to reach room temperature or become soft. Grate the cheese. Mix all ingredients together. Fill a cookie press with the dough. Line cookie sheets with waxed paper. Using press, put the dough onto cookie sheets and cut into the desired length. Cook in 325 degree oven for approximately 15 minutes. Allow to cool on brown paper.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute cabbage and onions in butter for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add more chicken bouillon cubes, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and butter.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and add syrup.
Combine the two.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake, it will set when cool.

title: eagle brand double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine. Layer milk, chocolate chips and peanut butter chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned; cool. Cut into bars.
Cover loosely.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: turkey sloppy joe
directions: Heat medium size nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add ground turkey; cook, breaking up turkey with wooden spoon, until no longer pink, about 6 minutes.
Spoon turkey into colander to drain excess fat.
Wipe skillet clean with paper towel.
Heat oil in skillet. Add onion, green pepper, oregano, cumin and chili powder.
Cook covered for 6 minutes until softened, stirring occasionally.
Add turkey, tomato sauce, barbecue sauce and olives, if using.
Bring to simmering uncovered; cook for 5 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: supreme brownies
directions: Melt together chocolate, butter and vanilla.
Beat in eggs and sugar.
Sift salt and flour together and beat into chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, frost.

title: hershey pie
directions: Crumble all 6 Hershey bars into bowl.
Microwave on High for approximately 1 minute or until softened.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix by hand thoroughly, until all chocolate is mixed in well. Fold mixture into pie crust and place in refrigerator for 2 hours or until firm.

title: brownies
directions: Blend cocoa, sugar, butter and eggs.
Add salt, vanilla and water.
Combine flour; spread into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with any chocolate frosting when completely cooled.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Boil 3 cups water.
Add bouillon, ham and peas, boiling for 3 minutes.
In small
bowl,
beat
eggs
and salt lightly. Stir into soup.
Cook to boiling.

title: brownies with caramel layer
directions: While baking, melt 50 caramels (14 ounce package) in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over partially-baked cake, then top with 1 cup chocolate chips, then remaining cake mix.
Bake another 15 to 25 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 1/2 full; let rise.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Yields about 30 rolls.

title: christmas pumpkin bread
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: quiche scandia
directions: Melt butter; saute onions and pepper until tender.
Add caraway seed.
Remove from heat.
Combine ham and cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Add bacon bits.
Beat eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Stir in onion mixture.
Pour 2 1/2 cups eggs mix into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand and cut in 4 to 6 wedges.

title: peanut sauce with grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix well.
Season to taste.
Store in a sealed container until ready to use.
Keeps for several weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat Jell-O, water and marshmallows over medium heat until marshmallows are melted.
Let cool.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine and boil chicken, cream of celery, cream of chicken and broth.
Separate and heat tortillas in hot shortening just long enough to soften.
Roll after being filled with meat mixture, cheese and onion.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Place in large greased casserole.
Top with more cheese.
Heat in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: turkey and stuffing pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pat stuffing evenly into 9-inch pie plate to form crust, building up sides to form rim.
Sprinkle turkey and cheese evenly over stuffing.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine, stirring until melted.
Add sugar and evaporated milk alternately.
Cook over low heat for 8 minutes.
When bubbles appear at pan sides, add the vanilla. Store refrigerated.
When ready to use, heat in a double boiler or in a microwave oven.

title: sweet and sour ham balls
directions: Mix ham loaf, crackers, eggs, milk and pineapple.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place balls in large baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over ham balls.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour, turning after 45 minutes.
Place in chafing dish to stay hot and serve.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, raisins and onion. In a small bowl, combine sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon and sunflower seeds; toss.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken log
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, liquid smoke and salt.
Using wax paper, sprinkle parsley flakes and chopped pecans on the paper. Shape chicken mixture into log shape; lay on top of flakes and pecans.
Roll over until all sides are coated.
Chill; serve on Ritz crackers.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix together in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: better than "pumpkin pie" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour dry cake mix in a bowl.
Remove 1 cup dry cake mix to a small bowl.
In the bowl containing the cake mix, add the oil and 1 egg.
Blend well and pat the mix evenly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hodgepodge
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and celery; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in boiling water until tender.
Add oleo, milk and cheese.
Thicken with flour, then add tomatoes.

title: aunt ruth's excellent cole slaw
directions: Finely chop the vegetables.
Heat and cool the rest of the ingredients.
Combine.
Will save.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs, salt, syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then turn down to 350° until done.

title: chicken rotelle
directions: Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in butter.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of mushroom soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add all of this to the cooked and drained spaghetti.
Melt Velveeta cheese and pour over spaghetti. Stir well and serve.

title: microwave coconut pie
directions: Mix well and microwave all the ingredients for 3 minutes. Add 1/2 stick of butter and stir. Microwave 3 to 4 minutes. Stir and pour in cooked pie shell.

title: homemade hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, salt and 1 cup flour.
Add liquid ingredients and beat well with a wooden spoon.
Add second cup flour and beat again.
Add remaining flour; stir well.
Set in a warm place and let rise at least 1 hour.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mixing
in baking dish, combine soup and lay chicken on top of soup mixture.
Mix stuffing mix with broth until moist. Pour over chicken.
Cover
with
foil and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: herman sourdough starter and coffee cake
directions: Place topping all over top of Herman Cake before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good, good!

title: frozen cheese torte
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Beat egg yolks; add salt, sugar and milk.
Cook in double boiler about 20 minutes.
Add gelatine to custard mixture.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand several hours to improve flavor.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, Milnot and melted butter and pour 1/2 in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Slice onion and separate rings. Clean and remove stems from mushrooms. Add onion rings and mushrooms to marinade. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Drain and serve with toothpicks.

title: wiener and kraut dogs
directions: In oblong baking dish, open number of hot dog buns desired. Spread each with hot dog relish.
On each bun, place heated wiener, chopped onions and top with a generous handful of kraut.
Cover these with chili and top with cheese.
Place in hot oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Pour into ovenproof dish. Arrange bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese tuna salad
directions: To marinate:
Mix all night before except noodles.
Cover. Add noodles and serve with filled eggs, olives and rolls.
Parsley for trim.
Serves 10.

title: turkey or chicken pot pie
directions: *Baking powder helps the crust to be crispier.

title: date-nut pudding
directions: Boil can of milk (in can) for 2 hours.
Be sure to keep top of can covered with water.
Water will need to be added during cooking.
Use medium heat, just enough to keep water boiling.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar. Add eggs (one at a time), mixing well.

title: cranberry spritzers
directions: For each serving, combine 3/4 cup cranberry juice cocktail and 1/4 cup club soda.
Serve over ice and garnish with lime slices. Serves 2.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Divide the pie crust into 4 equal pieces.
Place 1 apple onto dough and fill apple cavity with a bit of sugar and dash cinnamon to taste and pat of butter.
Wrap filled apple with dough and pinch closed at top.
Prepare remaining apples and place in baking dish.
On bottom of dish add 3/4 c. sugar, pat butter and 1/4 - 1/2 c. boiling water.
Bake until crust is done.
Combine 1 1/2 c. sugar, 3 Tbsp. flour and 1 1/2 c. milk in pan, stirring constantly until thickened, adding vanilla at the end.
Drizzle 'goop' over the top of each apple at serving time.
Serves 4.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add other ingredients.
Roll into fingers. Bake in moderate oven at 325° for about 30 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: mother's sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in large bowl, butter, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Stir until creamy.
Mix in another bowl, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Then pour this mixture into first mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts and bits.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown.

title: nutty bananas
directions: Finely chop some peanuts.
Give each child a plate with a small amount of chopped peanuts, a spoonful of yogurt and 1/2 of an unpeeled banana on it.
Have the children gradually peel their bananas and dip them first into the yogurt and then into the nuts before taking each bite.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually beating.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Freeze in 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Add mashed potatoes to scalded milk.
When cooled, add the yeast.
Mix thoroughly and add eggs.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Put in refrigerator for a couple of hours or overnight.
When ready to make rolls, punch down dough, form into rolls and let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yum, yum.

title: ritz delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Then add vanilla, Ritz crackers and nuts.
Spread into square Pyrex dish and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix curry and dry mustard.
Add mayonnaise and Maggi's seasoning.
Add parsley and onion.
Add lump crab meat.
Set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Serve with crackers or cocktail rye bread.

title: no bake pie crust
directions: Mix well and press in pie pan.
